WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.300 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.300 --> 00:00:06.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Imagine for a moment
historians of the distant

00:00:06.970 --> 00:00:10.780 align:middle line:84%
future grappling with the
question of which event best

00:00:10.780 --> 00:00:13.750 align:middle line:84%
described the
latter 20th century.

00:00:13.750 --> 00:00:17.140 align:middle line:84%
Would it be the explosion
of the first atomic bomb?

00:00:17.140 --> 00:00:19.360 align:middle line:84%
Or the emergence
of the internet?

00:00:19.360 --> 00:00:22.360 align:middle line:84%
Or even the astonishing
creation of 500 channels

00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:25.810 align:middle line:84%
of television without
anything much worth watching?

00:00:25.810 --> 00:00:27.160 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps.

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:30.310 align:middle line:84%
But then again, it just might
be the moment on June the 24th,

00:00:30.310 --> 00:00:35.500 align:middle line:84%
1947 when the pilot of a single
engine plane, a salesman named

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:37.870 align:middle line:84%
Kenneth Arnold,
was amazed to see

00:00:37.870 --> 00:00:40.450 align:middle line:84%
nine metallic objects
zooming past Mount

00:00:40.450 --> 00:00:43.240 align:middle line:90%
Rainier at impossible speeds.

00:00:43.240 --> 00:00:45.280 align:middle line:84%
Flying, he said,
like saucers would

00:00:45.280 --> 00:00:46.810 align:middle line:90%
if you skipped them on water.

00:00:46.810 --> 00:00:49.490 align:middle line:90%


00:00:49.490 --> 00:00:51.020 align:middle line:84%
In the following
weeks, thousands

00:00:51.020 --> 00:00:53.570 align:middle line:84%
of reports of flying
saucers flooded

00:00:53.570 --> 00:00:55.050 align:middle line:90%
in from much of the world.

00:00:55.050 --> 00:00:57.710 align:middle line:90%


00:00:57.710 --> 00:01:04.970 align:middle line:84%
In the shadow of the atomic
age, the era of UFOs had begun.

00:01:04.970 --> 00:01:08.710 align:middle line:84%
>> (SINGING) We lived
our little drama.

00:01:08.710 --> 00:01:12.230 align:middle line:90%
We kissed in a field of white.

00:01:12.230 --> 00:01:16.090 align:middle line:90%
And stars fell on Alabama.

00:01:16.090 --> 00:01:19.000 align:middle line:84%
>> But why is this event so
important that it should even

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:22.480 align:middle line:84%
be mentioned alongside the
most expressive milestones

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:24.130 align:middle line:90%
of the last century?

00:01:24.130 --> 00:01:26.590 align:middle line:84%
>> We bring you this special
radio television broadcast

00:01:26.590 --> 00:01:28.930 align:middle line:84%
in order to give you the
very latest information

00:01:28.930 --> 00:01:31.130 align:middle line:90%
on an amazing phenomenon.

00:01:31.130 --> 00:01:33.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, perhaps it's because
it was the first portent

00:01:33.970 --> 00:01:38.140 align:middle line:84%
of the time when our
world will change forever,

00:01:38.140 --> 00:01:42.100 align:middle line:84%
the cataclysmic instant when
certainty dawns that there are

00:01:42.100 --> 00:01:45.660 align:middle line:84%
others out there far
more advanced than us,

00:01:45.660 --> 00:01:48.700 align:middle line:84%
that we are not the pinnacle
of creation we have taken

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:53.650 align:middle line:84%
ourselves to be, that we are
only mere babes emerging from

00:01:53.650 --> 00:01:56.760 align:middle line:90%
our planetary cradle.

00:01:56.760 --> 00:01:59.040 align:middle line:84%
And perhaps it's important
because the story

00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:02.570 align:middle line:84%
of how the momentous question,
are we being visited,

00:02:02.570 --> 00:02:05.730 align:middle line:84%
arose, evolved, and was
eventually dismissed

00:02:05.730 --> 00:02:08.560 align:middle line:90%
by much of mainstream culture.

00:02:08.560 --> 00:02:10.410 align:middle line:84%
It is a story that
tells us a lot

00:02:10.410 --> 00:02:15.150 align:middle line:84%
about our civilization,
its hopes, its fears,

00:02:15.150 --> 00:02:16.245 align:middle line:90%
and its secret workings.

00:02:16.245 --> 00:02:24.960 align:middle line:90%


00:02:24.960 --> 00:02:27.420 align:middle line:84%
Like all good tales,
it needs a teller.

00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:29.460 align:middle line:90%
I was probably born for it.

00:02:29.460 --> 00:02:33.570 align:middle line:84%
I mean, look at those
hands pointing to the sky.

00:02:33.570 --> 00:02:35.890 align:middle line:10%
By age eight, I was
a boy astronomer,

00:02:35.890 --> 00:02:38.900 align:middle line:10%
a certified outer space junkie.

00:02:38.900 --> 00:02:41.760 align:middle line:84%
At 13, having precociously
chosen a career

00:02:41.760 --> 00:02:45.360 align:middle line:84%
path in astrophysics, I was
home from school for lunch

00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:47.460 align:middle line:84%
when I heard the tail
end of a news report

00:02:47.460 --> 00:02:50.460 align:middle line:84%
that a flying saucer had
been seen over the city

00:02:50.460 --> 00:02:53.710 align:middle line:84%
and children were
hiding under their beds.

00:02:53.710 --> 00:02:56.100 align:middle line:84%
I left early to walk
back to school eagerly

00:02:56.100 --> 00:02:57.045 align:middle line:90%
scanning the skies.

00:02:57.045 --> 00:03:00.380 align:middle line:90%


00:03:00.380 --> 00:03:02.030 align:middle line:84%
As I crossed the
playing field, I

00:03:02.030 --> 00:03:05.420 align:middle line:84%
spotted a red dot at
12:00 o'clock high.

00:03:05.420 --> 00:03:07.800 align:middle line:84%
And like a balloon,
it just sat there

00:03:07.800 --> 00:03:10.190 align:middle line:90%
not moving in the slightest.

00:03:10.190 --> 00:03:13.880 align:middle line:84%
When I came out later
for recess, it was gone.

00:03:13.880 --> 00:03:15.890 align:middle line:84%
That night, I went
to the public library

00:03:15.890 --> 00:03:20.760 align:middle line:84%
and took out every book I could
find about flying saucers.

00:03:20.760 --> 00:03:23.810 align:middle line:84%
I followed the subject
off and on ever since.

00:03:23.810 --> 00:03:25.780 align:middle line:84%
It's a strange and
fascinating mystery

00:03:25.780 --> 00:03:29.440 align:middle line:84%
that's hard to penetrate because
there are no good one stop

00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:32.170 align:middle line:90%
sources of information.

00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:34.090 align:middle line:84%
And the gold is
almost impossible

00:03:34.090 --> 00:03:35.405 align:middle line:90%
to separate from the dross.

00:03:35.405 --> 00:03:38.990 align:middle line:90%


00:03:38.990 --> 00:03:41.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Flying saucers have
invaded our planet.

00:03:41.270 --> 00:03:43.040 align:middle line:10%
>> The evidence,
as we shall see,

00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:46.580 align:middle line:10%
that some UFOs are from
somewhere else may be very

00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:47.930 align:middle line:10%
compelling.

00:03:47.930 --> 00:03:51.140 align:middle line:84%
But there's no smoking gun,
no landing on the White House

00:03:51.140 --> 00:03:53.172 align:middle line:90%
lawn.

00:03:53.172 --> 00:03:56.350 align:middle line:10%
>> They've set up an
electronic screen.

00:03:56.350 --> 00:03:59.500 align:middle line:10%
>> However, it is precisely
this absence of proof that has

00:03:59.500 --> 00:04:03.170 align:middle line:10%
allowed us to turn the UFO
phenomenon into a Rorschach ink

00:04:03.170 --> 00:04:06.700 align:middle line:10%
blot, an amorphous shape
on which we have projected

00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:09.340 align:middle line:10%
our hopes and fears.

00:04:09.340 --> 00:04:10.580 align:middle line:90%
We have mythologized it.

00:04:10.580 --> 00:04:13.160 align:middle line:90%
>> People of Earth, attention.

00:04:13.160 --> 00:04:15.350 align:middle line:84%
>> And in the process,
we've made it difficult,

00:04:15.350 --> 00:04:21.180 align:middle line:84%
if not impossible, to address
the question of its reality.

00:04:21.180 --> 00:04:24.090 align:middle line:84%
So this is the story
of how that happened.

00:04:24.090 --> 00:04:26.670 align:middle line:84%
And it begins, if
it has a beginning,

00:04:26.670 --> 00:04:33.750 align:middle line:84%
in the Pacific Northwest
on the 24th of June 1947.

00:04:33.750 --> 00:04:35.490 align:middle line:84%
While he was flying
home to Idaho

00:04:35.490 --> 00:04:37.980 align:middle line:84%
at the end of a business
trip, Kenneth Arnold

00:04:37.980 --> 00:04:41.070 align:middle line:84%
spent an hour searching for a
downed plane in the wilderness

00:04:41.070 --> 00:04:43.230 align:middle line:90%
of Washington state.

00:04:43.230 --> 00:04:45.990 align:middle line:84%
It was a bright sunny day
with perfect visibility,

00:04:45.990 --> 00:04:48.030 align:middle line:90%
but he had no luck.

00:04:48.030 --> 00:04:50.490 align:middle line:84%
Arnold sold forest
firefighting equipment

00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:54.780 align:middle line:84%
hopping about the Northwest
in his single engine CallAir.

00:04:54.780 --> 00:04:57.660 align:middle line:84%
As he turned towards home,
a blinding flash of light

00:04:57.660 --> 00:04:59.370 align:middle line:90%
caught his attention.

00:04:59.370 --> 00:05:02.070 align:middle line:84%
He located its source as
sunlight reflecting off

00:05:02.070 --> 00:05:04.980 align:middle line:84%
the metallic surface
of nine objects flying

00:05:04.980 --> 00:05:07.950 align:middle line:90%
south past Mount Rainier.

00:05:07.950 --> 00:05:11.070 align:middle line:84%
Arnold clocked their speed
over the 47 mile distance

00:05:11.070 --> 00:05:14.220 align:middle line:84%
to Mount Adams at
1,800 miles an hour,

00:05:14.220 --> 00:05:16.650 align:middle line:84%
almost four times
faster than any plane

00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:19.290 align:middle line:90%
known to be flying at the time.

00:05:19.290 --> 00:05:22.380 align:middle line:84%
Thinking they might be test
craft and 1,800 miles an hour

00:05:22.380 --> 00:05:25.170 align:middle line:84%
was too fast to
even contemplate,

00:05:25.170 --> 00:05:27.300 align:middle line:84%
he cut it to 1,200
miles an hour when

00:05:27.300 --> 00:05:30.720 align:middle line:84%
he reported what he'd
seen to a local newspaper.

00:05:30.720 --> 00:05:33.800 align:middle line:84%
The story was picked up
by the AP wire service,

00:05:33.800 --> 00:05:37.110 align:middle line:84%
and a headline writer
labeled them flying saucers.

00:05:37.110 --> 00:05:41.430 align:middle line:84%
>> He certainly had to be flying
in a very strong inversion.

00:05:41.430 --> 00:05:48.330 align:middle line:10%
The possibilities of there
being optical illusions

00:05:48.330 --> 00:05:53.140 align:middle line:10%
in that situation was something
that was a possibility.

00:05:53.140 --> 00:05:56.540 align:middle line:84%
Mirages do seem to be
moving and moving fast.

00:05:56.540 --> 00:05:58.790 align:middle line:10%
>> If it's a mountain mirage
which he's talking about,

00:05:58.790 --> 00:06:00.540 align:middle line:10%
they stay above the
tops of the mountains.

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:01.650 align:middle line:10%
They don't move laterally.

00:06:01.650 --> 00:06:03.570 align:middle line:10%
And they fade in and out.

00:06:03.570 --> 00:06:06.000 align:middle line:10%
And of course, they appear
to be inverted images

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:07.350 align:middle line:10%
of the top of the mountain.

00:06:07.350 --> 00:06:10.710 align:middle line:84%
Another more recent
explanation was geese.

00:06:10.710 --> 00:06:13.110 align:middle line:84%
The most recent one,
which has actually

00:06:13.110 --> 00:06:16.140 align:middle line:84%
led to a new
terminology, and Ufology

00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:20.610 align:middle line:84%
called pelicanism where you
take a explanation which

00:06:20.610 --> 00:06:23.990 align:middle line:84%
seems, to me anyway,
and a careful analysis

00:06:23.990 --> 00:06:25.052 align:middle line:90%
to be totally ridiculous.

00:06:25.052 --> 00:06:26.510 align:middle line:84%
And you push it as
hard as you can.

00:06:26.510 --> 00:06:29.990 align:middle line:84%
Ornithologists think
it could be pelicans.

00:06:29.990 --> 00:06:35.245 align:middle line:84%
Pelicans can be very bright
when reflecting sunlight.

00:06:35.245 --> 00:06:38.070 align:middle line:84%
>> And apparently, they
can move quite fast,

00:06:38.070 --> 00:06:41.700 align:middle line:84%
clocked on Arnold's watch
merrily gliding along at 1,800

00:06:41.700 --> 00:06:44.900 align:middle line:90%
miles an hour.

00:06:44.900 --> 00:06:46.820 align:middle line:84%
Meteors have also
been suggested.

00:06:46.820 --> 00:06:49.280 align:middle line:10%
Though, how meteors could
have traveled for 47

00:06:49.280 --> 00:06:51.680 align:middle line:10%
plus miles
horizontally has never

00:06:51.680 --> 00:06:53.930 align:middle line:10%
been explained,
nor how they could

00:06:53.930 --> 00:06:57.020 align:middle line:10%
resemble what Arnold drew.

00:06:57.020 --> 00:06:58.430 align:middle line:84%
Even though there
had been dozens

00:06:58.430 --> 00:07:01.940 align:middle line:84%
of local reports of strange
aerial objects in the preceding

00:07:01.940 --> 00:07:05.930 align:middle line:84%
months, Arnold's sightings
seemed to open a floodgate.

00:07:05.930 --> 00:07:08.630 align:middle line:10%
Within weeks, there were
more than 3,000 reports

00:07:08.630 --> 00:07:12.110 align:middle line:10%
from across North America
and around the world.

00:07:12.110 --> 00:07:14.150 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps, it's been
suggested, people

00:07:14.150 --> 00:07:18.040 align:middle line:84%
were collectively suffering
some trauma induced delusion,

00:07:18.040 --> 00:07:21.740 align:middle line:84%
a reaction to the threat of mass
destruction of a scale never

00:07:21.740 --> 00:07:22.540 align:middle line:90%
seen before.

00:07:22.540 --> 00:07:27.886 align:middle line:84%
>> Here is the motion picture
spectacle of all time,

00:07:27.886 --> 00:07:32.250 align:middle line:84%
a million tons of water
alive with deadly rays,

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:35.070 align:middle line:84%
awe inspiring in its
significance for man who

00:07:35.070 --> 00:07:38.700 align:middle line:84%
learned how to control the atom
but must now learn to control

00:07:38.700 --> 00:07:39.930 align:middle line:90%
himself.

00:07:39.930 --> 00:07:43.410 align:middle line:84%
>> In the midst of the
1947 flying saucer wave,

00:07:43.410 --> 00:07:47.040 align:middle line:84%
on July the 7th, the Army
Air Force Base at Roswell,

00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:51.300 align:middle line:84%
New Mexico, the home of the only
atomic bomb wing in the world,

00:07:51.300 --> 00:07:54.595 align:middle line:84%
issued a press release that it
had recovered a crashed disk.

00:07:54.595 --> 00:07:58.960 align:middle line:90%


00:07:58.960 --> 00:08:01.690 align:middle line:84%
The DJ at radio
station KGFL says

00:08:01.690 --> 00:08:03.850 align:middle line:84%
he was the first to get
the release from Walter

00:08:03.850 --> 00:08:06.130 align:middle line:90%
Haut, the base PR officer.

00:08:06.130 --> 00:08:08.290 align:middle line:10%
>> He hands me this release.

00:08:08.290 --> 00:08:09.625 align:middle line:10%
And he runs around.

00:08:09.625 --> 00:08:10.870 align:middle line:10%
He said, you got 30 minutes.

00:08:10.870 --> 00:08:13.120 align:middle line:10%
And he's practically
running out the door.

00:08:13.120 --> 00:08:16.540 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at it,
and I saw a flying saucer.

00:08:16.540 --> 00:08:18.220 align:middle line:90%
And I said, wait a minute.

00:08:18.220 --> 00:08:19.060 align:middle line:90%
Walter, you know.

00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:21.080 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going out
hollering after him.

00:08:21.080 --> 00:08:22.720 align:middle line:84%
He said, I got to
get back to the base.

00:08:22.720 --> 00:08:23.980 align:middle line:90%
You got 30 minutes.

00:08:23.980 --> 00:08:25.390 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't get him to stop.

00:08:25.390 --> 00:08:28.780 align:middle line:84%
So I had to wait because he said
he's going back to his office.

00:08:28.780 --> 00:08:31.030 align:middle line:84%
I had his number,
called, got him.

00:08:31.030 --> 00:08:33.552 align:middle line:84%
I said, Walter,
don't run this story.

00:08:33.552 --> 00:08:35.260 align:middle line:84%
If you do, you're
going to be in trouble.

00:08:35.260 --> 00:08:37.240 align:middle line:90%
They'll ship you off to Siberia.

00:08:37.240 --> 00:08:39.140 align:middle line:90%
I remember mentioning that.

00:08:39.140 --> 00:08:42.760 align:middle line:84%
That was a common
phrase in those days.

00:08:42.760 --> 00:08:44.090 align:middle line:90%
And he said, look.

00:08:44.090 --> 00:08:47.620 align:middle line:84%
He said, the old man
has cleared this.

00:08:47.620 --> 00:08:49.490 align:middle line:90%
It's OK to use it.

00:08:49.490 --> 00:08:52.110 align:middle line:84%
>> The Army Air Force has
announced that a flying disk

00:08:52.110 --> 00:08:55.570 align:middle line:84%
has been found and is now in
the possession of the Army.

00:08:55.570 --> 00:08:58.000 align:middle line:84%
>> About that time,
all hell broke loose.

00:08:58.000 --> 00:08:59.140 align:middle line:90%
The wire went dead.

00:08:59.140 --> 00:09:02.857 align:middle line:90%
And the phones began to ring.

00:09:02.857 --> 00:09:04.440 align:middle line:84%
>> And the cavalry
came to the rescue.

00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:07.060 align:middle line:90%


00:09:07.060 --> 00:09:09.640 align:middle line:84%
The next day at Fort Worth
headquarters, General Roger

00:09:09.640 --> 00:09:12.220 align:middle line:84%
Ramey informed a
breathless media

00:09:12.220 --> 00:09:14.890 align:middle line:84%
that the intelligence
officers of the only A bomb

00:09:14.890 --> 00:09:18.130 align:middle line:84%
base in the US arsenal had
mistaken a common weather

00:09:18.130 --> 00:09:21.550 align:middle line:84%
balloon for a crashed
flying saucer.

00:09:21.550 --> 00:09:24.780 align:middle line:84%
The press ran the story without
so much as an arched eyebrow.

00:09:24.780 --> 00:09:29.420 align:middle line:90%


00:09:29.420 --> 00:09:32.930 align:middle line:84%
And that was the last we'd
hear of Roswell for another 35

00:09:32.930 --> 00:09:35.600 align:middle line:84%
years, when it would
begin to blow up

00:09:35.600 --> 00:09:39.090 align:middle line:84%
into the culture with all
the power of an atomic bomb.

00:09:39.090 --> 00:09:48.740 align:middle line:90%


00:09:48.740 --> 00:09:51.710 align:middle line:84%
>> The long awaited unification
of the armed services comes

00:09:51.710 --> 00:09:52.700 align:middle line:90%
a step nearer.

00:09:52.700 --> 00:09:55.460 align:middle line:84%
>> A few weeks after Roswell,
the signing of the National

00:09:55.460 --> 00:09:58.940 align:middle line:84%
Securities Act reorganized the
Armed Forces and established

00:09:58.940 --> 00:10:01.400 align:middle line:84%
the CIA and the National
Security Council.

00:10:01.400 --> 00:10:03.980 align:middle line:84%
>> An iron curtain has
descended across continent.

00:10:03.980 --> 00:10:06.770 align:middle line:84%
>> The Cold War was
officially underway.

00:10:06.770 --> 00:10:09.680 align:middle line:84%
By August, flying saucer
reports had dropped,

00:10:09.680 --> 00:10:11.840 align:middle line:84%
and the press had pretty
well assigned the subject

00:10:11.840 --> 00:10:13.850 align:middle line:90%
to the crank file.

00:10:13.850 --> 00:10:17.510 align:middle line:84%
After all, no one had seen
or photographed one close up.

00:10:17.510 --> 00:10:19.940 align:middle line:84%
And the military was at
least publicly making

00:10:19.940 --> 00:10:21.980 align:middle line:90%
light of the whole idea.

00:10:21.980 --> 00:10:24.440 align:middle line:84%
But behind the scenes,
things were different.

00:10:24.440 --> 00:10:27.890 align:middle line:10%
>> This was something that the
intelligence community took

00:10:27.890 --> 00:10:30.020 align:middle line:10%
seriously immediately.

00:10:30.020 --> 00:10:33.230 align:middle line:10%
There was a desk called
the collections desk

00:10:33.230 --> 00:10:36.080 align:middle line:10%
in the Pentagon
that was interested

00:10:36.080 --> 00:10:40.550 align:middle line:10%
in dangerous possible
invasions of American airspace.

00:10:40.550 --> 00:10:42.470 align:middle line:10%
And this looked
like that well could

00:10:42.470 --> 00:10:45.080 align:middle line:10%
be what this was all about.

00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:48.140 align:middle line:84%
>> The Pentagon sent a request
for an evaluation to Air

00:10:48.140 --> 00:10:53.150 align:middle line:84%
Materiel Command at Wright
Field in Dayton, Ohio.

00:10:53.150 --> 00:10:55.370 align:middle line:10%
After a preliminary
intelligence gathering,

00:10:55.370 --> 00:10:57.350 align:middle line:10%
a memo was sent
back to the Pentagon

00:10:57.350 --> 00:11:00.980 align:middle line:10%
by Lieutenant General Nathan
Twining, the commanding officer

00:11:00.980 --> 00:11:02.260 align:middle line:10%
of Air Materiel Command.

00:11:02.260 --> 00:11:06.280 align:middle line:90%


00:11:06.280 --> 00:11:09.280 align:middle line:10%
It concluded that the phenomenon
is something real and not

00:11:09.280 --> 00:11:12.460 align:middle line:10%
visionary or fictitious
and that the extreme rates

00:11:12.460 --> 00:11:15.640 align:middle line:10%
of climb, maneuverability,
and motion, which

00:11:15.640 --> 00:11:17.800 align:middle line:10%
must be considered
evasive when sighted

00:11:17.800 --> 00:11:20.920 align:middle line:10%
or contacted by friendly
aircraft and radar,

00:11:20.920 --> 00:11:24.340 align:middle line:10%
lend belief to the possibility
that some of the objects

00:11:24.340 --> 00:11:25.390 align:middle line:10%
are controlled.

00:11:25.390 --> 00:11:31.080 align:middle line:84%
>> The natural belief was that
this must be Soviet technology.

00:11:31.080 --> 00:11:32.900 align:middle line:84%
The idea that it
was extraterrestrial

00:11:32.900 --> 00:11:36.080 align:middle line:84%
did not really come up
there at the very beginning.

00:11:36.080 --> 00:11:39.080 align:middle line:10%
>> Finally, Twining's memo
went on to recommend a detailed

00:11:39.080 --> 00:11:40.760 align:middle line:10%
codenamed study.

00:11:40.760 --> 00:11:43.730 align:middle line:84%
Project Sign was approved
at the end of December

00:11:43.730 --> 00:11:46.190 align:middle line:84%
as part of the Air Technical
Intelligence Center

00:11:46.190 --> 00:11:48.560 align:middle line:84%
at Wright Patterson
Air Force Base.

00:11:48.560 --> 00:11:51.620 align:middle line:84%
It immediately had to
contend with a disaster,

00:11:51.620 --> 00:11:54.840 align:middle line:84%
an Air Force plane had
gone down chasing a UFO.

00:11:54.840 --> 00:12:05.400 align:middle line:90%


00:12:05.400 --> 00:12:10.200 align:middle line:84%
On January 7, 1948, Kentucky Air
National Guard Captain Thomas

00:12:10.200 --> 00:12:14.170 align:middle line:84%
F. Mantell's F-51
fighter fell to earth.

00:12:14.170 --> 00:12:16.940 align:middle line:84%
He had been chasing a
strange object in the sky.

00:12:16.940 --> 00:12:23.870 align:middle line:90%


00:12:23.870 --> 00:12:26.900 align:middle line:84%
People have always seen
mysterious things in the sky

00:12:26.900 --> 00:12:30.830 align:middle line:84%
and attributed them
to unearthly beings.

00:12:30.830 --> 00:12:33.320 align:middle line:84%
In biblical times, it
would appear that angels

00:12:33.320 --> 00:12:38.150 align:middle line:90%
zipped about quite frequently.

00:12:38.150 --> 00:12:42.560 align:middle line:10%
In one Old Testament tale
often construed as a UFO event,

00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:45.620 align:middle line:10%
a fiery wheel carried
the prophet Ezekiel off

00:12:45.620 --> 00:12:48.530 align:middle line:10%
to the heavens.

00:12:48.530 --> 00:12:51.680 align:middle line:84%
From the Middle Ages up to
the Industrial Revolution,

00:12:51.680 --> 00:12:54.890 align:middle line:84%
ecclesiastical symbols found
their way into works of art

00:12:54.890 --> 00:13:01.400 align:middle line:84%
as celestial events interpreted
today by many as UFOs.

00:13:01.400 --> 00:13:04.280 align:middle line:84%
In the 18th century,
possibly as a reaction

00:13:04.280 --> 00:13:06.980 align:middle line:84%
to the rationality
of the Enlightenment,

00:13:06.980 --> 00:13:10.550 align:middle line:84%
there emerged a whole genre
of fantastic voyage tales.

00:13:10.550 --> 00:13:12.500 align:middle line:84%
>> The most prominent
one we know of is

00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:13.560 align:middle line:90%
"Gulliver's Travels."

00:13:13.560 --> 00:13:16.940 align:middle line:10%
But in the fantastic
voyage tales

00:13:16.940 --> 00:13:19.760 align:middle line:10%
of which there were
hundreds published,

00:13:19.760 --> 00:13:22.380 align:middle line:10%
people go traveling to all
kinds of different places,

00:13:22.380 --> 00:13:25.610 align:middle line:10%
including outer space.

00:13:25.610 --> 00:13:29.600 align:middle line:84%
>> In the last decades of the
19th century, many astronomers,

00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:32.570 align:middle line:84%
even such luminaries
as Percival Lowell,

00:13:32.570 --> 00:13:38.240 align:middle line:84%
observed a fantastic network of
canals on the surface of Mars.

00:13:38.240 --> 00:13:40.340 align:middle line:10%
Around the same time,
there were thousands

00:13:40.340 --> 00:13:42.560 align:middle line:10%
of reports of airships
throughout much

00:13:42.560 --> 00:13:45.170 align:middle line:10%
of North America,
almost all of which

00:13:45.170 --> 00:13:49.670 align:middle line:10%
are now accepted as hoaxes,
mistaken natural phenomena,

00:13:49.670 --> 00:13:53.660 align:middle line:10%
or the inventions of readership
hungry newspaper editors.

00:13:53.660 --> 00:13:56.510 align:middle line:10%
>> One newspaper in one town
would play a joke on another

00:13:56.510 --> 00:13:59.870 align:middle line:10%
town and say they would give
this elaborate article about

00:13:59.870 --> 00:14:03.170 align:middle line:10%
this fantastic airship
sighting in the other town.

00:14:03.170 --> 00:14:06.080 align:middle line:84%
The town where it actually
happens would say,

00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:08.570 align:middle line:90%
nobody here saw that thing.

00:14:08.570 --> 00:14:11.090 align:middle line:10%
It was a form of entertainment.

00:14:11.090 --> 00:14:13.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Moving from the
profane to the sacred,

00:14:13.400 --> 00:14:16.520 align:middle line:84%
at least one of the famous
apparitions of the Virgin Mary

00:14:16.520 --> 00:14:20.600 align:middle line:84%
at Fatima Portugal could
easily have been a classic UFO

00:14:20.600 --> 00:14:21.980 align:middle line:90%
sighting.

00:14:21.980 --> 00:14:23.840 align:middle line:84%
The clouds broke
and the sun appeared

00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:26.930 align:middle line:84%
as an opaque spinning
disk in the sky.

00:14:26.930 --> 00:14:30.020 align:middle line:84%
It was significantly
less bright than normal,

00:14:30.020 --> 00:14:34.510 align:middle line:84%
and it careened towards the
earth in a zigzag pattern.

00:14:34.510 --> 00:14:37.990 align:middle line:84%
But it could also read like
religious believers fired up

00:14:37.990 --> 00:14:42.870 align:middle line:84%
with faith staring
too long at the sun.

00:14:42.870 --> 00:14:44.820 align:middle line:10%
Though the notion of
life on other worlds

00:14:44.820 --> 00:14:48.480 align:middle line:10%
had been around since at least
the ancient Greek Atomos,

00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:51.330 align:middle line:10%
it was the scientific and
technological breakthrough

00:14:51.330 --> 00:14:55.470 align:middle line:10%
explosions of the late 19th
and early 20th centuries

00:14:55.470 --> 00:14:57.870 align:middle line:10%
that provided fertile
ground for the idea

00:14:57.870 --> 00:15:01.150 align:middle line:10%
to take wide hold
in popular culture.

00:15:01.150 --> 00:15:04.280 align:middle line:10%
Pulp science fiction magazines
filled the newsstands,

00:15:04.280 --> 00:15:07.500 align:middle line:10%
their covers often showing
prescient illustrations

00:15:07.500 --> 00:15:11.010 align:middle line:10%
of what would be
described in the 1947 wave

00:15:11.010 --> 00:15:11.955 align:middle line:10%
as flying saucers.

00:15:11.955 --> 00:15:17.790 align:middle line:90%


00:15:17.790 --> 00:15:20.820 align:middle line:84%
>> The broadcasting system and
its affiliated stations present

00:15:20.820 --> 00:15:24.450 align:middle line:84%
Orson Welles and the Mercury
Theater on the Air in "The War

00:15:24.450 --> 00:15:28.050 align:middle line:90%
of the Worlds" by H.G. Wells.

00:15:28.050 --> 00:15:32.280 align:middle line:84%
>> We know now that in the
early years of the 20th century,

00:15:32.280 --> 00:15:35.950 align:middle line:84%
this world was being watched
closely by intelligences

00:15:35.950 --> 00:15:38.040 align:middle line:90%
greater than man.

00:15:38.040 --> 00:15:41.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Orson Welles' 1938 Halloween
broadcast sent thousands

00:15:41.820 --> 00:15:44.200 align:middle line:90%
of listeners into a panic.

00:15:44.200 --> 00:15:45.884 align:middle line:90%
>> There's something happening.

00:15:45.884 --> 00:15:48.020 align:middle line:84%
Some shape is rising
out of the pit.

00:15:48.020 --> 00:15:49.680 align:middle line:90%
--the advancing men.

00:15:49.680 --> 00:15:50.970 align:middle line:90%
It strikes them head on.

00:15:50.970 --> 00:15:52.910 align:middle line:84%
Oh lord, they're
turning into flames.

00:15:52.910 --> 00:15:56.130 align:middle line:84%
>> It quite clearly showed that
beneath the surface of things

00:15:56.130 --> 00:16:00.030 align:middle line:84%
extraterrestrial lay
something darkly visceral,

00:16:00.030 --> 00:16:04.080 align:middle line:84%
the fear of the other, a
theme that would emerge again

00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:06.233 align:middle line:90%
in those early days of 1948.

00:16:06.233 --> 00:16:08.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Ladies and gentlemen,
due to circumstances beyond

00:16:08.400 --> 00:16:12.030 align:middle line:90%
our control, we are unable--

00:16:12.030 --> 00:16:14.820 align:middle line:84%
>> The Air Force accident
investigators concluded that

00:16:14.820 --> 00:16:18.630 align:middle line:84%
Captain Thomas F. Mantell had
blacked out from lack of oxygen

00:16:18.630 --> 00:16:21.140 align:middle line:90%
at 25,000 feet.

00:16:21.140 --> 00:16:23.040 align:middle line:84%
Five minutes earlier,
he had radioed

00:16:23.040 --> 00:16:25.590 align:middle line:84%
that he had spotted the
object high above him

00:16:25.590 --> 00:16:28.380 align:middle line:84%
and was climbing to
get a closer look.

00:16:28.380 --> 00:16:31.390 align:middle line:84%
He described it as metallic
and tremendous in size.

00:16:31.390 --> 00:16:40.160 align:middle line:90%


00:16:40.160 --> 00:16:42.650 align:middle line:84%
After Mantell apparently
lost consciousness,

00:16:42.650 --> 00:16:46.790 align:middle line:84%
his plane had climbed to 30,000
feet when it stalled and began

00:16:46.790 --> 00:16:48.300 align:middle line:90%
its death spiral to earth.

00:16:48.300 --> 00:16:54.780 align:middle line:90%


00:16:54.780 --> 00:16:57.630 align:middle line:84%
News that a pilot had died
chasing a flying saucer

00:16:57.630 --> 00:17:00.060 align:middle line:90%
shot across the wires.

00:17:00.060 --> 00:17:01.980 align:middle line:84%
The Air Force
investigators announced

00:17:01.980 --> 00:17:04.740 align:middle line:84%
that Mantell had died
chasing the planet

00:17:04.740 --> 00:17:08.099 align:middle line:84%
Venus, an explanation
that seemed ridiculous

00:17:08.099 --> 00:17:10.560 align:middle line:84%
given his description
and eyewitness

00:17:10.560 --> 00:17:13.630 align:middle line:84%
accounts of a large, slow
moving, cone-shaped object.

00:17:13.630 --> 00:17:18.280 align:middle line:90%


00:17:18.280 --> 00:17:21.099 align:middle line:84%
In the early '50s, the Air
Force's Project Blue Book

00:17:21.099 --> 00:17:24.520 align:middle line:84%
revisited the case and
concluded that the object

00:17:24.520 --> 00:17:28.150 align:middle line:84%
was a top secret Navy
skyhook balloon used

00:17:28.150 --> 00:17:29.620 align:middle line:90%
to study cosmic rays.

00:17:29.620 --> 00:17:34.330 align:middle line:90%


00:17:34.330 --> 00:17:37.240 align:middle line:84%
However, it was under the
shadow cast by the tragedy

00:17:37.240 --> 00:17:40.450 align:middle line:84%
that the members of the
Air Force's Project Sign

00:17:40.450 --> 00:17:43.180 align:middle line:84%
began their investigation
into flying saucers.

00:17:43.180 --> 00:17:46.690 align:middle line:90%


00:17:46.690 --> 00:17:50.740 align:middle line:84%
Throughout the winter and spring
of 1948 at Wright Patterson Air

00:17:50.740 --> 00:17:54.820 align:middle line:84%
Force Base in building T2, they
began to grapple with the fact

00:17:54.820 --> 00:17:56.860 align:middle line:84%
that whatever they were,
the saucers weren't

00:17:56.860 --> 00:17:59.590 align:middle line:84%
foreign or secret
domestic technology.

00:17:59.590 --> 00:18:02.190 align:middle line:90%


00:18:02.190 --> 00:18:04.110 align:middle line:84%
Investigators went
out into the field

00:18:04.110 --> 00:18:06.340 align:middle line:84%
to quietly talk to
people, many of them

00:18:06.340 --> 00:18:08.145 align:middle line:90%
military who had filed reports.

00:18:08.145 --> 00:18:11.690 align:middle line:90%


00:18:11.690 --> 00:18:14.700 align:middle line:84%
By March, they had over
300 made by observers

00:18:14.700 --> 00:18:16.130 align:middle line:90%
they considered competent.

00:18:16.130 --> 00:18:19.560 align:middle line:90%


00:18:19.560 --> 00:18:23.030 align:middle line:84%
By summer, a debate was
raging within the Sign team

00:18:23.030 --> 00:18:26.981 align:middle line:84%
whether some of the objects
reported were extraterrestrial.

00:18:26.981 --> 00:18:29.570 align:middle line:90%


00:18:29.570 --> 00:18:32.750 align:middle line:84%
Then one night in July,
an extraordinary incident

00:18:32.750 --> 00:18:35.170 align:middle line:90%
unfolded.

00:18:35.170 --> 00:18:39.370 align:middle line:84%
>> The case that turned the
corner for Project Sign has

00:18:39.370 --> 00:18:42.040 align:middle line:84%
gone by the name of the
Chiles-Whitted case,

00:18:42.040 --> 00:18:45.760 align:middle line:84%
out of the two airline pilots
that were the prime witnesses

00:18:45.760 --> 00:18:47.970 align:middle line:90%
in the case.

00:18:47.970 --> 00:18:51.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Eastern Airlines flight
576 was 20 miles south

00:18:51.600 --> 00:18:56.370 align:middle line:84%
of Montgomery, Alabama at 2:45
in the morning of July the 24th

00:18:56.370 --> 00:18:59.820 align:middle line:84%
when Captain Clarence S. Chiles
and first officer John B.

00:18:59.820 --> 00:19:03.210 align:middle line:84%
Whitted saw an elongated
wingless craft flash

00:19:03.210 --> 00:19:09.860 align:middle line:84%
by their plane at what they
estimated as 700 miles an hour.

00:19:09.860 --> 00:19:13.220 align:middle line:84%
Both men describe the object
as metallic with two lighted

00:19:13.220 --> 00:19:14.060 align:middle line:90%
rows of windows.

00:19:14.060 --> 00:19:18.860 align:middle line:90%


00:19:18.860 --> 00:19:21.440 align:middle line:84%
On Pentagon instruction,
Sign investigators

00:19:21.440 --> 00:19:25.070 align:middle line:84%
hurriedly flew off to
interview Chiles and Whitted.

00:19:25.070 --> 00:19:27.470 align:middle line:84%
They were impressed with
the two men's certainty

00:19:27.470 --> 00:19:31.070 align:middle line:84%
that what they saw was
a manufactured object.

00:19:31.070 --> 00:19:33.860 align:middle line:84%
The Sign team was also
aware of a report the week

00:19:33.860 --> 00:19:37.730 align:middle line:84%
before from the Netherlands
of a similar two-tiered craft

00:19:37.730 --> 00:19:40.820 align:middle line:84%
and other reports from across
Europe of wingless planes.

00:19:40.820 --> 00:19:43.340 align:middle line:90%


00:19:43.340 --> 00:19:46.070 align:middle line:84%
Within days of the
Chiles-Whitted sighting,

00:19:46.070 --> 00:19:49.310 align:middle line:84%
the Sign team had
committed to a conclusion.

00:19:49.310 --> 00:19:53.930 align:middle line:84%
>> The reason why Project
Sign saw this case as being

00:19:53.930 --> 00:19:58.310 align:middle line:84%
extraterrestrial was that this
was an object flying freely

00:19:58.310 --> 00:20:01.580 align:middle line:84%
and apparently maneuverably
in our environment that had no

00:20:01.580 --> 00:20:02.870 align:middle line:90%
wings.

00:20:02.870 --> 00:20:07.040 align:middle line:84%
So where would the lift for
a piloted craft of some kind

00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:08.930 align:middle line:90%
come from?

00:20:08.930 --> 00:20:12.620 align:middle line:84%
What they knew as
technologists at Wright Patt

00:20:12.620 --> 00:20:15.110 align:middle line:84%
was the only way such
an object could fly

00:20:15.110 --> 00:20:18.837 align:middle line:84%
is if it had a tremendously
powerful energy source.

00:20:18.837 --> 00:20:20.420 align:middle line:84%
And the only thing
they could think of

00:20:20.420 --> 00:20:22.820 align:middle line:84%
would be something
like nuclear, but they

00:20:22.820 --> 00:20:25.880 align:middle line:84%
knew that they had
nothing nuclear

00:20:25.880 --> 00:20:27.590 align:middle line:90%
and no one else did either.

00:20:27.590 --> 00:20:29.270 align:middle line:84%
They were stuck
with a conclusion

00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:31.080 align:middle line:84%
that this was an
extraterrestrial device.

00:20:31.080 --> 00:20:34.100 align:middle line:90%


00:20:34.100 --> 00:20:37.020 align:middle line:10%
>> As traffic backed up with
employees leaving Wright Patt

00:20:37.020 --> 00:20:39.570 align:middle line:10%
at the end of the
midsummer workdays,

00:20:39.570 --> 00:20:42.210 align:middle line:10%
the Sign team was hunkered down
writing what they must have

00:20:42.210 --> 00:20:45.240 align:middle line:10%
seen as one of the most
important documents ever

00:20:45.240 --> 00:20:46.470 align:middle line:10%
written.

00:20:46.470 --> 00:20:49.320 align:middle line:10%
It was an estimate of
the situation required

00:20:49.320 --> 00:20:53.970 align:middle line:10%
of all military investigations
once they reach a conclusion.

00:20:53.970 --> 00:20:56.400 align:middle line:84%
The estimate was then
sent to the Pentagon

00:20:56.400 --> 00:20:59.910 align:middle line:84%
where it circulated to
a very mixed reaction.

00:20:59.910 --> 00:21:02.550 align:middle line:84%
>> The majority of the people
in the Pentagon at the time

00:21:02.550 --> 00:21:06.480 align:middle line:84%
thought that this was not
a message that they wanted

00:21:06.480 --> 00:21:09.930 align:middle line:84%
to send out into the world
or even into the military

00:21:09.930 --> 00:21:13.500 align:middle line:84%
community itself, that this
was just too strange and too

00:21:13.500 --> 00:21:14.610 align:middle line:90%
dangerous.

00:21:14.610 --> 00:21:17.970 align:middle line:84%
It was like a unknown
wild card that they

00:21:17.970 --> 00:21:19.860 align:middle line:84%
didn't want to let
psychologically

00:21:19.860 --> 00:21:23.110 align:middle line:90%
loose within their people.

00:21:23.110 --> 00:21:25.930 align:middle line:84%
>> The estimate worked its way
up to the desk of Air Force

00:21:25.930 --> 00:21:29.590 align:middle line:84%
Chief of Staff Hoyt Vandenberg,
who was, we can assume,

00:21:29.590 --> 00:21:32.070 align:middle line:90%
thrilled to see.

00:21:32.070 --> 00:21:33.810 align:middle line:84%
As what he did with
the estimate is

00:21:33.810 --> 00:21:35.820 align:middle line:84%
a crucial juncture
in this story,

00:21:35.820 --> 00:21:39.240 align:middle line:84%
it's worthwhile to consider
his decision options.

00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:42.120 align:middle line:84%
He could, one, reject the
estimate straight away

00:21:42.120 --> 00:21:47.100 align:middle line:84%
and bury its conclusions,
two, order further study,

00:21:47.100 --> 00:21:49.560 align:middle line:84%
which would serve to keep
its conclusions alive

00:21:49.560 --> 00:21:53.240 align:middle line:84%
with the possibility
of leaks, or, three,

00:21:53.240 --> 00:21:56.220 align:middle line:84%
accept the conclusions,
which would

00:21:56.220 --> 00:21:58.440 align:middle line:84%
mean admitting to the
Congress, the president,

00:21:58.440 --> 00:22:01.230 align:middle line:84%
and the American people
that the Air Force was

00:22:01.230 --> 00:22:03.570 align:middle line:84%
powerless to prevent
extraterrestrials

00:22:03.570 --> 00:22:07.500 align:middle line:84%
of unknown origin and,
worse, unknown intent

00:22:07.500 --> 00:22:09.405 align:middle line:84%
from overflying
the United States.

00:22:09.405 --> 00:22:18.970 align:middle line:90%


00:22:18.970 --> 00:22:21.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Researchers who believe
that a flying saucer crashed

00:22:21.700 --> 00:22:24.970 align:middle line:84%
at Roswell are of the opinion
that Vandenberg's decision was

00:22:24.970 --> 00:22:27.770 align:middle line:90%
made to perpetuate a cover up.

00:22:27.770 --> 00:22:30.580 align:middle line:84%
But Roswell is not
necessary to understand

00:22:30.580 --> 00:22:32.920 align:middle line:90%
why the estimate was quashed.

00:22:32.920 --> 00:22:35.860 align:middle line:90%
Simple convenience suffices.

00:22:35.860 --> 00:22:38.840 align:middle line:84%
The idea it advocated
was dangerous.

00:22:38.840 --> 00:22:42.220 align:middle line:84%
The effect on the
population unpredictable.

00:22:42.220 --> 00:22:47.200 align:middle line:84%
Authority fears and loathes
one thing above all.

00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:49.630 align:middle line:84%
Vandenberg let it be
known to the Sign team

00:22:49.630 --> 00:22:53.200 align:middle line:84%
