saucers don't exist Project

00:23:24.870 --> 00:23:27.390 align:middle line:84%
Grudge, a series
of sightings called

00:23:27.390 --> 00:23:30.570 align:middle line:84%
the green fireballs began
over sensitive military

00:23:30.570 --> 00:23:32.010 align:middle line:90%
installations in New Mexico.

00:23:32.010 --> 00:23:34.700 align:middle line:90%


00:23:34.700 --> 00:23:37.450 align:middle line:10%
They were seen by dozens of
scientists at the Los Alamos

00:23:37.450 --> 00:23:40.330 align:middle line:10%
Nuclear Research
Installation and by hundreds

00:23:40.330 --> 00:23:42.040 align:middle line:10%
of military personnel.

00:23:42.040 --> 00:23:47.750 align:middle line:84%
At least 39 reports were sent
to Grudge by April of '49.

00:23:47.750 --> 00:23:50.150 align:middle line:84%
There was great concern in
the scientific community

00:23:50.150 --> 00:23:51.950 align:middle line:90%
about what they were.

00:23:51.950 --> 00:23:54.200 align:middle line:84%
But Project Grudge,
true to its name,

00:23:54.200 --> 00:23:58.860 align:middle line:84%
