would never be the same.

00:24:54.670 --> 00:24:59.450 align:middle line:90%


00:24:59.450 --> 00:25:01.970 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, through
the rest of 1949,

00:25:01.970 --> 00:25:04.100 align:middle line:84%
the team at Project
Grudge did their best

00:25:04.100 --> 00:25:08.090 align:middle line:84%
to shoot down any
and all sightings.

00:25:08.090 --> 00:25:10.670 align:middle line:84%
They were aided in their
mission by their new astronomer

00:25:10.670 --> 00:25:13.350 align:middle line:90%
consultant, J. Allen Hynek.

00:25:13.350 --> 00:25:15.620 align:middle line:90%
Hynek was very skeptical.

00:25:15.620 --> 00:25:18.830 align:middle line:84%
From the beginning, he
assumed that all reports

00:25:18.830 --> 00:25:21.590 align:middle line:84%
