conventional terms.

00:25:21.590 --> 00:25:23.210 align:middle line:10%
And that is, in
fact, what he did.

00:25:23.210 --> 00:25:25.880 align:middle line:10%
That was his function
for the Air Force.

00:25:25.880 --> 00:25:27.740 align:middle line:10%
They would take the
cases to him, say,

00:25:27.740 --> 00:25:28.970 align:middle line:10%
we can't explain this.

00:25:28.970 --> 00:25:30.770 align:middle line:84%
We can't trace a
weather balloon.

00:25:30.770 --> 00:25:35.850 align:middle line:84%
Is this a comet, a
meteor, a planet?

00:25:35.850 --> 00:25:40.130 align:middle line:84%
And Hynek would provide
the explanation.

00:25:40.130 --> 00:25:43.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Donald Keyhoe's True Magazine
article appeared just before

00:25:43.250 --> 00:25:46.360 align:middle line:90%
New Year's 1950.

00:25:46.360 --> 00:25:50.750 align:middle line:84%
It was the largest selling
issue in the magazine's history.

00:25:50.750 --> 00:25:52.220 align:middle line:10%
>> This was a sensation.

00:25:52.220 --> 00:25:55.400 align:middle line:10%
This article got press
coverage all over the world.

00:25:55.400 --> 00:25:57.890 align:middle line:84%
Keyhoe concluded from
