>> (SINGING) And
lead us on to love.

00:33:59.070 --> 00:34:02.040 align:middle line:84%
>> In the spring, Life Magazine
openly wondered if we have

00:34:02.040 --> 00:34:06.209 align:middle line:84%
visitors from space and became
as talked about as the 1950

00:34:06.209 --> 00:34:07.009 align:middle line:90%
True article.

00:34:07.009 --> 00:34:10.159 align:middle line:90%


00:34:10.159 --> 00:34:14.239 align:middle line:84%
The New York Times, hostile to
the whole idea from the start,

00:34:14.239 --> 00:34:17.750 align:middle line:84%
sneered that the subject had as
much reality as the Loch Ness

00:34:17.750 --> 00:34:19.685 align:middle line:90%
Monster.

00:34:19.685 --> 00:34:23.409 align:middle line:10%
And the first debunker appeared.

00:34:23.409 --> 00:34:27.010 align:middle line:84%
Donald Menzel was a
prestigious Harvard astronomer

00:34:27.010 --> 00:34:30.010 align:middle line:84%
who employed all his political
and media connections

00:34:30.010 --> 00:34:33.820 align:middle line:84%
to discourage anyone from
taking the subject seriously.

00:34:33.820 --> 00:34:39.639 align:middle line:10%
>> He had enough cachet as
a Harvard astronomer to get

00:34:39.639 --> 00:34:43.540 align:middle line:10%
into Time Magazine and places
like that with his idea that it

00:34:43.540 --> 00:34:48.280 align:middle line:10%
was all oddball radar
reflections and plasma effects

00:34:48.280 --> 00:34:51.969 align:middle line:10%
and a bunch of
misinterpreted nonsense.

00:34:51.969 --> 00:34:54.699 align:middle line:84%
>> According to Ed Ruppelt,
Menzel and his strained

00:34:54.699 --> 00:34:58.120 align:middle line:84%
explanations garnered little
more than contempt at Air Force

00:34:58.120 --> 00:34:59.650 align:middle line:90%
Intelligence.

00:34:59.650 --> 00:35:03.310 align:middle line:84%
They had their hands full
with the practical problem.

00:35:03.310 --> 00:35:06.880 align:middle line:84%
The great saucer wave of
1952 had broken in June

00:35:06.880 --> 00:35:10.120 align:middle line:84%
sending everyone
scurrying to keep up.

00:35:10.120 --> 00:35:15.070 align:middle line:84%
Reports for the month totaled
144, the highest number ever.

00:35:15.070 --> 00:35:18.630 align:middle line:84%
July would more
than triple that.

00:35:18.630 --> 00:35:21.300 align:middle line:84%
On July 14th, the
pilot and co-pilot

00:35:21.300 --> 00:35:24.240 align:middle line:84%
of a Pan Am flight off
the coast of Virginia

00:35:24.240 --> 00:35:29.310 align:middle line:84%
watched six bright orange disks
flying in a line, flip on edge,

00:35:29.310 --> 00:35:32.760 align:middle line:84%
get joined in their echelon
by another two disks,

00:35:32.760 --> 00:35:34.800 align:middle line:84%
and disappear off
into the distance

00:35:34.800 --> 00:35:37.990 align:middle line:84%
at a speed they clocked at
an astounding 12,000 miles

00:35:37.990 --> 00:35:38.790 align:middle line:90%
an hour.

00:35:38.790 --> 00:35:41.480 align:middle line:90%


00:35:41.480 --> 00:35:44.840 align:middle line:84%
Donald Menzel would toss out
many explanations for the Nash

00:35:44.840 --> 00:35:48.210 align:middle line:90%
Fortenberry incident.

00:35:48.210 --> 00:35:51.060 align:middle line:84%
That old standby
meteors was one.

00:35:51.060 --> 00:35:53.520 align:middle line:84%
It's an interesting
irony that the scientists

00:35:53.520 --> 00:35:56.970 align:middle line:84%
of the 18th century
couldn't accept that rocks

00:35:56.970 --> 00:36:00.340 align:middle line:90%
could fall from the sky.

00:36:00.340 --> 00:36:04.300 align:middle line:84%
Menzel also suggested
searchlights playing on clouds.

00:36:04.300 --> 00:36:06.610 align:middle line:84%
Although a quick check of
the weather would have shown

00:36:06.610 --> 00:36:08.880 align:middle line:90%
it was a cloudless night.

00:36:08.880 --> 00:36:11.620 align:middle line:84%
Then he tossed out
reflections in the cockpit

00:36:11.620 --> 00:36:15.460 align:middle line:84%
glass of lighted cigarettes
in the passenger cabin.

00:36:15.460 --> 00:36:18.760 align:middle line:84%
And finally, in what may have
been a stretch for the ages,

00:36:18.760 --> 00:36:22.120 align:middle line:84%
fireflies trapped between the
windshield panes of glass.

00:36:22.120 --> 00:36:25.440 align:middle line:90%


00:36:25.440 --> 00:36:27.310 align:middle line:84%
But the Nash
Fortenberry incident

00:36:27.310 --> 00:36:31.300 align:middle line:84%
was just a harbinger of what was
to come less than a week later

00:36:31.300 --> 00:36:34.270 align:middle line:84%
with a series of events
that would completely change

00:36:34.270 --> 00:36:36.803 align:middle line:90%
the history of the phenomena.

00:36:36.803 --> 00:36:42.370 align:middle line:90%


00:36:42.370 --> 00:36:46.670 align:middle line:84%
The midsummer of '52 was
when everything changed.

00:36:46.670 --> 00:36:50.000 align:middle line:84%
>> We're talking about
massive wave of sightings.

00:36:50.000 --> 00:36:52.670 align:middle line:84%
And they were getting 20
or more sightings per day.

00:36:52.670 --> 00:36:57.950 align:middle line:84%
They are flying all up
and down the East coast.

00:36:57.950 --> 00:37:01.460 align:middle line:10%
And some people actually
predicted, because of the way

00:37:01.460 --> 00:37:03.380 align:middle line:10%
they were doing it,
that they would probably

00:37:03.380 --> 00:37:05.750 align:middle line:10%
show up in Washington DC.

00:37:05.750 --> 00:37:10.540 align:middle line:84%
And there, in the middle
of July, they did.

00:37:10.540 --> 00:37:13.870 align:middle line:84%
>> A cluster of seven blips 10
miles southwest of the capital

00:37:13.870 --> 00:37:18.640 align:middle line:84%
was first noticed at 11:40 PM
Saturday July 19th on the long

00:37:18.640 --> 00:37:22.630 align:middle line:84%
range radar at Washington
National Airport.

00:37:22.630 --> 00:37:26.820 align:middle line:84%
One of the operators looked out
and saw a bright orange light.

00:37:26.820 --> 00:37:29.520 align:middle line:84%
When the blips started showing
up over the White House,

00:37:29.520 --> 00:37:32.400 align:middle line:84%
Harry Barnes, the senior
traffic controller,

00:37:32.400 --> 00:37:36.250 align:middle line:84%
called Andrews Air Force
Base 10 miles to the east.

00:37:36.250 --> 00:37:39.720 align:middle line:84%
An Andrews controller was soon
seeing bright orange objects

00:37:39.720 --> 00:37:42.670 align:middle line:90%
flashing through the sky.

00:37:42.670 --> 00:37:45.190 align:middle line:84%
As the runways at Andrews
were under repair,

00:37:45.190 --> 00:37:48.800 align:middle line:84%
jets would have to be dispatched
from Newcastle Air Force Base

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:52.570 align:middle line:90%
30 minutes away in Delaware.

00:37:52.570 --> 00:37:55.900 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, a Capital Airlines
flight taking off from National

00:37:55.900 --> 00:38:00.250 align:middle line:84%
was vectored towards some
radar blips to the west.

00:38:00.250 --> 00:38:03.970 align:middle line:84%
As they approached the area,
they saw nothing unusual.

00:38:03.970 --> 00:38:06.670 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, a bluish white
light flashed in front of them

00:38:06.670 --> 00:38:09.280 align:middle line:90%
on a 25 degree dive.

00:38:09.280 --> 00:38:11.230 align:middle line:84%
Then another one
shot from behind them

00:38:11.230 --> 00:38:13.790 align:middle line:90%
zooming up and out of sight.

00:38:13.790 --> 00:38:16.860 align:middle line:84%
In the next seven minutes,
they watched seven more lights

00:38:16.860 --> 00:38:21.570 align:middle line:84%
all being simultaneously tracked
on the radar back at National.

00:38:21.570 --> 00:38:23.530 align:middle line:84%
The most spectacular
incident happened

00:38:23.530 --> 00:38:26.080 align:middle line:84%
when National tower
informed Andrews

00:38:26.080 --> 00:38:28.750 align:middle line:84%
that they had a target
right over the base.

00:38:28.750 --> 00:38:34.600 align:middle line:84%
The operators looked out and
saw huge a fiery orange sphere.

00:38:34.600 --> 00:38:37.060 align:middle line:84%
When the jets finally
arrived from Delaware,

00:38:37.060 --> 00:38:39.820 align:middle line:84%
all the blips disappeared
only to return

00:38:39.820 --> 00:38:42.160 align:middle line:90%
when the jets departed.

00:38:42.160 --> 00:38:44.530 align:middle line:84%
Harry Barnes would later
tell the newspapers

00:38:44.530 --> 00:38:46.510 align:middle line:84%
that he felt the
targets were somehow

00:38:46.510 --> 00:38:48.790 align:middle line:90%
aware of their communications.

00:38:48.790 --> 00:38:51.040 align:middle line:84%
>> A little dance went
on for a couple of times.

00:38:51.040 --> 00:38:53.770 align:middle line:90%
And it boggled everybody's mind.

00:38:53.770 --> 00:38:57.850 align:middle line:84%
The night of Saturday July
19th, dramatic though it was,

00:38:57.850 --> 00:39:01.540 align:middle line:90%
would just be the warm up act.

00:39:01.540 --> 00:39:05.200 align:middle line:10%
The following Saturday at
9:30, both radars at Washington

00:39:05.200 --> 00:39:07.420 align:middle line:10%
National and the one
at Andrews started

00:39:07.420 --> 00:39:10.450 align:middle line:10%
getting returns as
visual sightings poured

00:39:10.450 --> 00:39:13.360 align:middle line:10%
in from all over the area.

00:39:13.360 --> 00:39:15.490 align:middle line:84%
Al Chop, the public
information officer

00:39:15.490 --> 00:39:19.320 align:middle line:84%
at the Pentagon for UFOs who
was a confirmed skeptic when

00:39:19.320 --> 00:39:22.150 align:middle line:84%
he started the job, was
called out to the tower

00:39:22.150 --> 00:39:25.990 align:middle line:84%
at Washington
National at midnight.

00:39:25.990 --> 00:39:28.660 align:middle line:84%
There was total confusion
as reports of objects

00:39:28.660 --> 00:39:30.910 align:middle line:90%
were coming in droves.

00:39:30.910 --> 00:39:34.570 align:middle line:84%
Some of the radar blips
were solid, some less so.

00:39:34.570 --> 00:39:37.300 align:middle line:84%
One airline pilot, after
making multiple passes

00:39:37.300 --> 00:39:39.640 align:middle line:84%
over the spot he'd
been vectored to,

00:39:39.640 --> 00:39:42.680 align:middle line:84%
concluded the target was a
river boat plying the Potomac.

00:39:42.680 --> 00:39:45.580 align:middle line:90%


00:39:45.580 --> 00:39:47.110 align:middle line:90%
Two jets had arrived earlier.

00:39:47.110 --> 00:39:49.760 align:middle line:84%
And again, the objects
had disappeared.

00:39:49.760 --> 00:39:54.310 align:middle line:84%
Now a Chop was present,
a second pair arrived.

00:39:54.310 --> 00:39:57.520 align:middle line:84%
One was vectored to an area 10
miles out of the city, which

00:39:57.520 --> 00:40:00.740 align:middle line:90%
showed radar targets.

00:40:00.740 --> 00:40:03.890 align:middle line:84%
As he approached, he
described four white globes

00:40:03.890 --> 00:40:08.570 align:middle line:84%
and began to close in for a
much anticipated intercept.

00:40:08.570 --> 00:40:11.690 align:middle line:84%
But as Chop and the controllers
watched on the scope,

00:40:11.690 --> 00:40:15.380 align:middle line:84%
the object shot right at
the jet and surrounded it.

00:40:15.380 --> 00:40:17.840 align:middle line:84%
According to Chop,
the pilot radioed them

00:40:17.840 --> 00:40:20.630 align:middle line:84%
for instructions asking,
what do I do now?

00:40:20.630 --> 00:40:23.430 align:middle line:90%


00:40:23.430 --> 00:40:26.490 align:middle line:84%
Then the glowing
orbs zipped off.

00:40:26.490 --> 00:40:32.740 align:middle line:84%
After that, Al Chop was no
longer a skeptic about UFOs.

00:40:32.740 --> 00:40:35.320 align:middle line:84%
Monday's banner headline
in the Washington Post

00:40:35.320 --> 00:40:37.580 align:middle line:84%
caused mounting concern
of a public panic.

00:40:37.580 --> 00:40:40.380 align:middle line:90%


00:40:40.380 --> 00:40:43.650 align:middle line:84%
On Tuesday morning, the largest
and longest Air Force press

00:40:43.650 --> 00:40:47.640 align:middle line:84%
conference since the Second
World War took place.

00:40:47.640 --> 00:40:51.030 align:middle line:84%
The brass, all carefree
smiles, suggested

00:40:51.030 --> 00:40:52.710 align:middle line:84%
that a temperature
inversion could

00:40:52.710 --> 00:40:54.840 align:middle line:84%
have caused the radars
to pick up ground

00:40:54.840 --> 00:40:58.230 align:middle line:90%
vehicles as airborne objects.

00:40:58.230 --> 00:41:01.260 align:middle line:84%
The majority of the
media ran with this.

00:41:01.260 --> 00:41:04.560 align:middle line:10%
But behind the walls of the
Pentagon in the offices of Air

00:41:04.560 --> 00:41:07.770 align:middle line:10%
Force Intelligence,
all explanations

00:41:07.770 --> 00:41:11.430 align:middle line:10%
were still very
much on the table.

00:41:11.430 --> 00:41:13.260 align:middle line:84%
During the height of
the flap, Ed Ruppelt

00:41:13.260 --> 00:41:15.960 align:middle line:84%
had taken a call from
Harry Truman's military aid

00:41:15.960 --> 00:41:19.580 align:middle line:84%
General Robert P. Landry
demanding answers.

00:41:19.580 --> 00:41:22.110 align:middle line:84%
>> And he told them that they
didn't know what they had

00:41:22.110 --> 00:41:23.900 align:middle line:90%
on their hands.

00:41:23.900 --> 00:41:27.250 align:middle line:84%
Well, it took Harry
Truman one day

00:41:27.250 --> 00:41:31.960 align:middle line:84%
to order Landry to go to the
Joint Intelligence Committee

00:41:31.960 --> 00:41:35.440 align:middle line:90%
and to order a study of this.

00:41:35.440 --> 00:41:38.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Aside from the question
of what had just happened,

00:41:38.320 --> 00:41:42.240 align:middle line:84%
the Washington flap had caused a
major communications breakdown.

00:41:42.240 --> 00:41:47.800 align:middle line:84%
>> The hysteria, the jamming of
the telephone lines where you

00:41:47.800 --> 00:41:50.890 align:middle line:90%
couldn't even call the Pentagon.

00:41:50.890 --> 00:41:54.370 align:middle line:84%
>> When the request at the Joint
Intelligence Committee came

00:41:54.370 --> 00:42:01.420 align:middle line:84%
down to take a look at UFOs, the
logical place for that request

00:42:01.420 --> 00:42:07.810 align:middle line:84%
to be studied was some agency
other than the one studying it

00:42:07.810 --> 00:42:10.750 align:middle line:84%
already, which
was the Air Force.

00:42:10.750 --> 00:42:13.933 align:middle line:90%
And so, they picked the CIA.

00:42:13.933 --> 00:42:16.510 align:middle line:10%
>> Fred Durant, a
rocket engineer,

00:42:16.510 --> 00:42:20.170 align:middle line:10%
was in the CIA's Office of
Scientific Intelligence.

00:42:20.170 --> 00:42:22.210 align:middle line:10%
>> The ball was handed to me.

00:42:22.210 --> 00:42:25.850 align:middle line:10%
>> Did the CIA have concerns
about the competence of Blue

00:42:25.850 --> 00:42:26.650 align:middle line:10%
Book?

00:42:26.650 --> 00:42:31.540 align:middle line:84%
>> As far as competence, well,
it was obvious it do not have

00:42:31.540 --> 00:42:36.000 align:middle line:84%
professional competency
above an engineer.

00:42:36.000 --> 00:42:38.470 align:middle line:84%
>> While Ruppelt was an
aeronautical engineer,

00:42:38.470 --> 00:42:41.000 align:middle line:84%
he was just a lowly
reserve lieutenant.

00:42:41.000 --> 00:42:43.480 align:middle line:84%
And his understaffed
little project

00:42:43.480 --> 00:42:47.290 align:middle line:84%
was now in the glaring spotlight
of the entire Cold War security

00:42:47.290 --> 00:42:49.320 align:middle line:90%
apparatus.

00:42:49.320 --> 00:42:52.800 align:middle line:84%
Durant and his cohorts from
the CIA went to Wright Patt

00:42:52.800 --> 00:42:56.680 align:middle line:84%
to examine Blue
Book's methodology.

00:42:56.680 --> 00:42:59.320 align:middle line:84%
After sniffing around,
the CIA decided

00:42:59.320 --> 00:43:03.010 align:middle line:84%
to have a scientific panel
to evaluate the Air Force

00:43:03.010 --> 00:43:05.170 align:middle line:90%
evidence.

00:43:05.170 --> 00:43:09.340 align:middle line:84%
>> CIA wanted to keep this
as an internal project,

00:43:09.340 --> 00:43:11.740 align:middle line:84%
which they had
complete control over.

00:43:11.740 --> 00:43:15.850 align:middle line:84%
So rather than going to a
good high tech science group,

00:43:15.850 --> 00:43:17.320 align:middle line:84%
out of which we
might have gotten

00:43:17.320 --> 00:43:23.170 align:middle line:84%
a rather nice estimate again
of what the phenomenon was,

00:43:23.170 --> 00:43:28.840 align:middle line:84%
what happened was that they went
to internal CIA consultants.

00:43:28.840 --> 00:43:31.480 align:middle line:84%
The most well-known
of which, and a person

00:43:31.480 --> 00:43:35.350 align:middle line:84%
who had been chief consulting
scientist for the CIA

00:43:35.350 --> 00:43:40.030 align:middle line:84%
in the past, was a guy named
Doctor Bob Robertson, H.P.

00:43:40.030 --> 00:43:44.830 align:middle line:84%
Robertson, a nuclear
scientist, more or less

00:43:44.830 --> 00:43:47.350 align:middle line:90%
a mathematician from Cal Tech.

00:43:47.350 --> 00:43:50.200 align:middle line:84%
>> The Robertson panel met
in secret over four days

00:43:50.200 --> 00:43:55.240 align:middle line:84%
at the beginning of January 1953
and spent a total of 12 hours

00:43:55.240 --> 00:43:59.140 align:middle line:84%
reviewing in depth only eight
cases of the hundreds that Blue

00:43:59.140 --> 00:44:02.920 align:middle line:90%
Book had on file as unknowns.

00:44:02.920 --> 00:44:05.110 align:middle line:84%
As an example of
their in-depth review,

00:44:05.110 --> 00:44:07.420 align:middle line:84%
they concluded that
the Great Falls Montana

00:44:07.420 --> 00:44:10.780 align:middle line:84%
film taken by Nick
Mariana was of two fighter

00:44:10.780 --> 00:44:14.950 align:middle line:84%
jets in the area, this, despite
Mariana's claim he observed

00:44:14.950 --> 00:44:17.320 align:middle line:90%
the jets a few minutes later.

00:44:17.320 --> 00:44:19.570 align:middle line:84%
And had Ruppelt's
reinvestigation

00:44:19.570 --> 00:44:22.570 align:middle line:84%
that concluded the planes
were nowhere as near Mariana

00:44:22.570 --> 00:44:24.820 align:middle line:90%
as the objects on the film.

00:44:24.820 --> 00:44:27.220 align:middle line:84%
>> The Robertson panel
report was basically there

00:44:27.220 --> 00:44:30.070 align:middle line:84%
for everybody to
sign the next day.

00:44:30.070 --> 00:44:33.430 align:middle line:10%
And it had already been passed
to the chief of Air Force

00:44:33.430 --> 00:44:36.160 align:middle line:10%
Intelligence for his approval.

00:44:36.160 --> 00:44:39.610 align:middle line:10%
>> The Robertson panel concluded
that as reasonable explanations

00:44:39.610 --> 00:44:42.070 align:middle line:10%
could be suggested
for most sightings,

00:44:42.070 --> 00:44:46.030 align:middle line:10%
all sightings might be
explained in a similar manner.

00:44:46.030 --> 00:44:49.210 align:middle line:10%
It also recommended that to
eliminate national security

00:44:49.210 --> 00:44:53.830 align:middle line:10%
communications problems and the
communists using UFO hysteria

00:44:53.830 --> 00:44:57.040 align:middle line:10%
to their advantage that
the subject be debunked

00:44:57.040 --> 00:44:59.740 align:middle line:10%
and ridiculed, so the
public would no longer

00:44:59.740 --> 00:45:01.630 align:middle line:10%
take it seriously.

00:45:01.630 --> 00:45:04.960 align:middle line:84%
>> If you wanted to eliminate a
national security problem with

00:45:04.960 --> 00:45:09.610 align:middle line:84%
this, you needed to change the
attitude of the American public

00:45:09.610 --> 00:45:11.670 align:middle line:90%
to this phenomena.

00:45:11.670 --> 00:45:14.740 align:middle line:84%
And the only effective
way of doing that

00:45:14.740 --> 00:45:17.230 align:middle line:90%
was to make it be a joke.

00:45:17.230 --> 00:45:22.810 align:middle line:84%
There was no science in this
science committee report.

00:45:22.810 --> 00:45:25.310 align:middle line:84%
It was all about
national security.

00:45:25.310 --> 00:45:29.200 align:middle line:90%


00:45:29.200 --> 00:45:30.990 align:middle line:84%
>> The world's
first hydrogen bomb,

00:45:30.990 --> 00:45:32.950 align:middle line:84%
housed in this
barn like building,

00:45:32.950 --> 00:45:35.320 align:middle line:84%
was to be exploded on
a tiny target island.

00:45:35.320 --> 00:45:37.960 align:middle line:84%
>> In the wake of the Robertson
panel's recommendations,

00:45:37.960 --> 00:45:40.390 align:middle line:84%
Project Blue Book
was repurposed.

00:45:40.390 --> 00:45:41.470 align:middle line:90%
Its funding shrank.

00:45:41.470 --> 00:45:44.550 align:middle line:84%
And Ruppelt soon
left the service.

00:45:44.550 --> 00:45:46.360 align:middle line:84%
Blue Book continued,
but its role now

00:45:46.360 --> 00:45:48.580 align:middle line:84%
seemed to be to carry
out the Robertson panel's

00:45:48.580 --> 00:45:51.970 align:middle line:90%
recommendations and debunk UFOs.

00:45:51.970 --> 00:45:53.710 align:middle line:84%
Behind the walls
of the Pentagon,

00:45:53.710 --> 00:45:57.040 align:middle line:84%
the extraterrestrial debate
at the top levels of Air Force

00:45:57.040 --> 00:46:00.140 align:middle line:90%
Intelligence petered out.

00:46:00.140 --> 00:46:02.390 align:middle line:84%
The Washington flap
had rattled the windows

00:46:02.390 --> 00:46:05.660 align:middle line:84%
in the corridors of
power and raised concerns

00:46:05.660 --> 00:46:10.660 align:middle line:84%
about public hysteria in the
perilous times of the Cold War.

00:46:10.660 --> 00:46:14.570 align:middle line:84%
A brief period of open
inquiry had come to an end,

00:46:14.570 --> 00:46:19.838 align:middle line:84%
and a dark curtain of denial
had once again descended.

00:46:19.838 --> 00:46:25.560 align:middle line:84%
>> (SINGING) See the
USA in your Chevrolet.

00:46:25.560 --> 00:46:27.430 align:middle line:90%
America' asking you to call.

00:46:27.430 --> 00:46:29.940 align:middle line:84%
>> By the early '50s, even
with a new administration

00:46:29.940 --> 00:46:33.570 align:middle line:84%
in Washington, it was evident
that any revelations about

00:46:33.570 --> 00:46:37.560 align:middle line:84%
the UFO mystery would not be
forthcoming from government.

00:46:37.560 --> 00:46:39.510 align:middle line:84%
And civilian
investigation groups

00:46:39.510 --> 00:46:43.350 align:middle line:84%
were started up by people
who wanted answers.

00:46:43.350 --> 00:46:45.540 align:middle line:84%
But the day was also
dawning on people

00:46:45.540 --> 00:46:51.260 align:middle line:84%
who claimed to already know
the answers, the contactees.

00:46:51.260 --> 00:46:54.070 align:middle line:84%
In 1952, a man born
in Poland named

00:46:54.070 --> 00:46:57.670 align:middle line:84%
George Adamski had walked
out into the Mojave Desert

00:46:57.670 --> 00:47:02.590 align:middle line:84%
and met Orthon, a man born on
Venus or so Adamski claimed.

00:47:02.590 --> 00:47:05.860 align:middle line:84%
And many thousands
would believe him.

00:47:05.860 --> 00:47:09.700 align:middle line:10%
>> It didn't take very long once
people started seeing flying

00:47:09.700 --> 00:47:13.330 align:middle line:10%
saucers to present stories
that saviors were actually

00:47:13.330 --> 00:47:16.570 align:middle line:10%
descending from the sky, which
is where saviors usually come

00:47:16.570 --> 00:47:18.280 align:middle line:10%
from anyway.

00:47:18.280 --> 00:47:21.680 align:middle line:84%
But in this case, they came
in a technological form

00:47:21.680 --> 00:47:22.700 align:middle line:90%
in a spaceship.

00:47:22.700 --> 00:47:25.360 align:middle line:84%
Georgia Adamski's
visiting aliens

00:47:25.360 --> 00:47:32.530 align:middle line:84%
incorporated so much angelic
imagery that it's obvious.

00:47:32.530 --> 00:47:35.980 align:middle line:84%
>> As his fame grew, Adamski was
soon joined by others claiming

00:47:35.980 --> 00:47:39.520 align:middle line:84%
physical and telepathic
contact with the space brothers

00:47:39.520 --> 00:47:43.360 align:middle line:84%
and sisters and writing books
about their joy rides with them

00:47:43.360 --> 00:47:45.690 align:middle line:90%
to other planets.

00:47:45.690 --> 00:47:49.180 align:middle line:84%
1954 saw their first
convention at Giant Rock

00:47:49.180 --> 00:47:50.360 align:middle line:90%
in the Mojave Desert.

00:47:50.360 --> 00:47:53.300 align:middle line:90%


00:47:53.300 --> 00:47:55.290 align:middle line:10%
The contactee
movement was a feast

00:47:55.290 --> 00:48:00.820 align:middle line:10%
for the media, an easy
snack of assorted nuts.

00:48:00.820 --> 00:48:03.340 align:middle line:84%
This tended to confirm
the suspicions of many

00:48:03.340 --> 00:48:07.570 align:middle line:84%
that there was nothing to
flying saucers of any substance.

00:48:07.570 --> 00:48:09.850 align:middle line:10%
Among the serious
UFO research groups,

00:48:09.850 --> 00:48:12.790 align:middle line:10%
the need was seen for a
high profile organization

00:48:12.790 --> 00:48:17.060 align:middle line:10%
in Washington DC to lobby
Congress and press for hearings

00:48:17.060 --> 00:48:17.860 align:middle line:10%
into UFOs.

00:48:17.860 --> 00:48:20.430 align:middle line:10%


00:48:20.430 --> 00:48:23.710 align:middle line:10%
The National Investigations
Committee on Aerial Phenomena

00:48:23.710 --> 00:48:28.860 align:middle line:10%
or NICAP was formed in 1956.

00:48:28.860 --> 00:48:32.160 align:middle line:84%
It was soon being directed
by that UFO crusader Donald

00:48:32.160 --> 00:48:32.960 align:middle line:90%
Keyhoe.

00:48:32.960 --> 00:48:35.730 align:middle line:90%


00:48:35.730 --> 00:48:39.620 align:middle line:10%
>> Keyhoe was a
master at publicity.

00:48:39.620 --> 00:48:42.110 align:middle line:10%
He was good on radio.

00:48:42.110 --> 00:48:43.730 align:middle line:10%
He was good on television.

00:48:43.730 --> 00:48:46.260 align:middle line:84%
He had a certain kind
of personal charisma.

00:48:46.260 --> 00:48:48.510 align:middle line:90%
He was intensely sincere.

00:48:48.510 --> 00:48:52.970 align:middle line:84%
He attracted all kinds of people
with solid professional and

00:48:52.970 --> 00:48:55.055 align:middle line:84%
middle class
credentials to lobby

00:48:55.055 --> 00:48:56.180 align:middle line:90%
for congressional hearings.

00:48:56.180 --> 00:48:59.970 align:middle line:90%


00:48:59.970 --> 00:49:02.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Today, a new
moon is in the sky.

00:49:02.100 --> 00:49:05.490 align:middle line:84%
>> The Soviet launch of Sputnik
shocked America and ushered

00:49:05.490 --> 00:49:09.990 align:middle line:84%
in the 1957 wave, notable for
the many close range vehicle

00:49:09.990 --> 00:49:15.570 align:middle line:84%
interference cases and
reports of landed craft.

00:49:15.570 --> 00:49:17.550 align:middle line:84%
By the end of the
decade, the numbers

00:49:17.550 --> 00:49:21.840 align:middle line:84%
at the contactee conventions
at Giant Rock were dwindling.

00:49:21.840 --> 00:49:24.120 align:middle line:10%
But the bright eyed
naivete of the '50s

00:49:24.120 --> 00:49:25.980 align:middle line:10%
wouldn't come to
a definitive end

00:49:25.980 --> 00:49:30.750 align:middle line:10%
until the events of
November the 22nd, 1963.

00:49:30.750 --> 00:49:34.560 align:middle line:84%
Dark forces now seemed to
be lurking in the shadows,

00:49:34.560 --> 00:49:37.470 align:middle line:84%
and they underscored
the four year UFO wave

00:49:37.470 --> 00:49:39.900 align:middle line:90%
that began the same year.

00:49:39.900 --> 00:49:43.140 align:middle line:84%
Visual sightings of
distant UFOs were

00:49:43.140 --> 00:49:47.820 align:middle line:84%
about to become up
close and personal.

00:49:47.820 --> 00:49:51.390 align:middle line:84%
In mid-decade, one such strange
and disturbing encounter

00:49:51.390 --> 00:49:53.980 align:middle line:90%
came to light.

00:49:53.980 --> 00:49:56.080 align:middle line:84%
It would gain even
greater significance

00:49:56.080 --> 00:49:58.870 align:middle line:84%
two decades later
because it involved

00:49:58.870 --> 00:50:02.470 align:middle line:84%
missing time, hypnotically
recovered memories

00:50:02.470 --> 00:50:06.250 align:middle line:84%
of being abducted, and
the taking of samples

00:50:06.250 --> 00:50:08.530 align:middle line:84%
from the human
reproductive system.

00:50:08.530 --> 00:50:11.950 align:middle line:10%
>> In a way, it's really
extraordinarily important

00:50:11.950 --> 00:50:15.610 align:middle line:10%
for the fact that it
laid down the terms,

00:50:15.610 --> 00:50:17.770 align:middle line:10%
although they didn't
know that at the time,

00:50:17.770 --> 00:50:21.100 align:middle line:10%
for what the shape the
phenomenon was about to take.

00:50:21.100 --> 00:50:23.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Betty and Barney Hill,
returning from a vacation

00:50:23.710 --> 00:50:26.230 align:middle line:84%
through the White
Mountains of New Hampshire,

00:50:26.230 --> 00:50:29.830 align:middle line:84%
had seen a UFO following
them at close range.

00:50:29.830 --> 00:50:33.930 align:middle line:84%
Inexplicably, they arrived
home three hours late.

00:50:33.930 --> 00:50:35.790 align:middle line:84%
Betty called her
sister and niece over

00:50:35.790 --> 00:50:39.880 align:middle line:84%
to see some strange things
that had occurred that night.

00:50:39.880 --> 00:50:46.030 align:middle line:10%
>> The tops of Barney's
shoes were deeply gouged.

00:50:46.030 --> 00:50:50.530 align:middle line:10%
We saw the watches that had
stopped working that night.

00:50:50.530 --> 00:50:56.020 align:middle line:84%
We saw the highly magnetic
spots, very shiny spots

00:50:56.020 --> 00:50:58.540 align:middle line:90%
on the trunk of the car.

00:50:58.540 --> 00:51:00.520 align:middle line:84%
>> In separate
hypnosis sessions,

00:51:00.520 --> 00:51:03.850 align:middle line:84%
a terrifying ordeal was recalled
where the couple was taken

00:51:03.850 --> 00:51:08.345 align:middle line:84%
aboard a craft and subjected
to something like examinations.

00:51:08.345 --> 00:51:09.720 align:middle line:84%
>> A needle was
put in her navel.

00:51:09.720 --> 00:51:14.385 align:middle line:84%
They told her it was some
sort of pregnancy test.

00:51:14.385 --> 00:51:15.760 align:middle line:84%
And a sperm sample
was definitely

00:51:15.760 --> 00:51:18.070 align:middle line:84%
taken from Barnney Hill
even though that was not

00:51:18.070 --> 00:51:21.880 align:middle line:84%
mentioned in the book, because
it was seen as unseemly.

00:51:21.880 --> 00:51:25.570 align:middle line:10%
>> One story just not
a phenomenon make.

00:51:25.570 --> 00:51:28.360 align:middle line:10%
And what you're looking
for, of course, is patterns.

00:51:28.360 --> 00:51:30.340 align:middle line:84%
And with Barney
and Betty Hill, we

00:51:30.340 --> 00:51:33.490 align:middle line:84%
didn't quite know how to
approach it, how to study it,

00:51:33.490 --> 00:51:36.930 align:middle line:84%
how to understand
what was happening.

00:51:36.930 --> 00:51:39.930 align:middle line:84%
>> As strange as it was,
the Hills' incident was just

00:51:39.930 --> 00:51:44.100 align:middle line:84%
an inexplicable blip on
the UFO map of the decade.

00:51:44.100 --> 00:51:47.130 align:middle line:10%
If the mid '60s wave
had a climactic event,

00:51:47.130 --> 00:51:50.310 align:middle line:10%
it was the infamous
swamp gas incident.

00:51:50.310 --> 00:51:54.390 align:middle line:10%
>> Not that it was the
most fabulous of UFO cases,

00:51:54.390 --> 00:51:58.380 align:middle line:10%
but it occurred at sort of an
emotional peak that had a lot

00:51:58.380 --> 00:52:03.480 align:middle line:10%
of momentum to it as far as
the public was concerned.

00:52:03.480 --> 00:52:07.620 align:middle line:84%
>> In March of '66, a localized
wave had hit southern Michigan

00:52:07.620 --> 00:52:09.690 align:middle line:90%
lasting over a week.

00:52:09.690 --> 00:52:11.790 align:middle line:84%
In one of the more
spectacular incidents,

00:52:11.790 --> 00:52:14.160 align:middle line:84%
40 people, including
a dozen policemen,

00:52:14.160 --> 00:52:17.660 align:middle line:84%
chased after something
flying around a swamp.

00:52:17.660 --> 00:52:19.770 align:middle line:84%
And less than a mile
away over this field,

00:52:19.770 --> 00:52:22.830 align:middle line:84%
a patrolman reported a
low flying object approach

00:52:22.830 --> 00:52:26.780 align:middle line:90%
and zip 10 feet above his car.

00:52:26.780 --> 00:52:28.660 align:middle line:84%
But it was what
happened the next night

00:52:28.660 --> 00:52:31.790 align:middle line:84%
at a girls' dormitory at
Hillsdale College that

00:52:31.790 --> 00:52:35.560 align:middle line:90%
sparked a media frenzy.

00:52:35.560 --> 00:52:39.040 align:middle line:84%
Over the course of an evening,
87 coeds, their dorm mother,

00:52:39.040 --> 00:52:41.440 align:middle line:84%
and a civil defense
director watched something

00:52:41.440 --> 00:52:44.890 align:middle line:84%
closely resembling what
the policemen saw zip

00:52:44.890 --> 00:52:47.670 align:middle line:90%
around the arboretum out back.

00:52:47.670 --> 00:52:50.080 align:middle line:90%
First to spot it was Jo Wilson.

00:52:50.080 --> 00:52:53.230 align:middle line:84%
She called her roommate
Sarah Robechek to the window.

00:52:53.230 --> 00:52:55.660 align:middle line:90%
>> There were three lights.

00:52:55.660 --> 00:52:57.460 align:middle line:84%
And this one was bigger
than the other two.

00:52:57.460 --> 00:53:00.050 align:middle line:84%
And it pulsated from
white through yellow

00:53:00.050 --> 00:53:01.540 align:middle line:90%
to orange to red and back.

00:53:01.540 --> 00:53:03.930 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen
anything move that fast.

00:53:03.930 --> 00:53:05.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Did it have any sound?

00:53:05.230 --> 00:53:06.020 align:middle line:10%
>> Not that we could hear.

00:53:06.020 --> 00:53:07.570 align:middle line:10%
>> I don't remember
any sound that night.

00:53:07.570 --> 00:53:08.500 align:middle line:10%
>> It was very quiet.

00:53:08.500 --> 00:53:09.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Nothing.

00:53:09.370 --> 00:53:10.900 align:middle line:90%
And it was a mild spring night.

00:53:10.900 --> 00:53:13.520 align:middle line:90%
It was very mild and cold.

00:53:13.520 --> 00:53:15.530 align:middle line:90%
>> What happens the next day?

00:53:15.530 --> 00:53:19.640 align:middle line:10%
>> CBS, ABC, and NBC fly
into Hillsdale, Michigan.

00:53:19.640 --> 00:53:22.460 align:middle line:10%
>> Oh, they loved
that, didn't they?

00:53:22.460 --> 00:53:25.310 align:middle line:10%
>> I do know when we got
back to our room that day,

00:53:25.310 --> 00:53:29.420 align:middle line:10%
there was a CBS camera man
with his giant camera sitting

00:53:29.420 --> 00:53:32.630 align:middle line:10%
on my desk with the camera
pointing out to the arb saying

00:53:32.630 --> 00:53:34.370 align:middle line:10%
he was staying all night.

00:53:34.370 --> 00:53:37.820 align:middle line:10%
And a TV camera
back then was huge.

00:53:37.820 --> 00:53:40.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Blue Book sent Allen Hynek
into the fray to deal with

00:53:40.790 --> 00:53:43.970 align:middle line:84%
the media and to
find an explanation.

00:53:43.970 --> 00:53:48.500 align:middle line:84%
>> On the basis of a very brief,
literally over the phone piece

00:53:48.500 --> 00:53:53.000 align:middle line:84%
of information, and sort of an
accident where he was talking

00:53:53.000 --> 00:53:56.630 align:middle line:84%
to a friend from the
scientific community of his,

00:53:56.630 --> 00:54:01.640 align:middle line:84%
this friend wondered about
the possibility of swamp gas

00:54:01.640 --> 00:54:08.000 align:middle line:84%
as being ignited and showing
kind of a bulbous glowing ball

00:54:08.000 --> 00:54:11.300 align:middle line:84%
that people unfamiliar with
it might be confused by.

00:54:11.300 --> 00:54:15.920 align:middle line:84%
And Allen, not to
his great credit,

00:54:15.920 --> 00:54:18.800 align:middle line:84%
decided that that's what he
was going to go with on this.

00:54:18.800 --> 00:54:20.870 align:middle line:84%
And he came out in
public with the idea

00:54:20.870 --> 00:54:22.745 align:middle line:84%
that this was a
swamp gas phenomenon.

00:54:22.745 --> 00:54:24.620 align:middle line:10%
>> Where we were looking,
there was no swamp.

00:54:24.620 --> 00:54:26.150 align:middle line:84%
>> It was an arboretum,
for goodness sakes.

00:54:26.150 --> 00:54:27.200 align:middle line:90%
>> The arboretum, yeah.

00:54:27.200 --> 00:54:29.590 align:middle line:84%
>> They would go in
there and prune and mow.

00:54:29.590 --> 00:54:31.820 align:middle line:90%
And it was pretty.

00:54:31.820 --> 00:54:33.770 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't swampy.

00:54:33.770 --> 00:54:36.590 align:middle line:84%
>> He stuck his
foot in his mouth.

00:54:36.590 --> 00:54:38.870 align:middle line:84%
And people didn't let
him get away with it.

00:54:38.870 --> 00:54:41.840 align:middle line:84%
And people were railing on
him across the whole country

00:54:41.840 --> 00:54:45.800 align:middle line:84%
right on up to Congress
and Jerry Ford,

00:54:45.800 --> 00:54:47.420 align:middle line:84%
who was speaker of
the House at that

00:54:47.420 --> 00:54:51.590 align:middle line:84%
time and a rather important
man who felt that his Michigan

00:54:51.590 --> 00:54:55.070 align:middle line:84%
constituency had been
publicly embarrassed

00:54:55.070 --> 00:54:57.590 align:middle line:84%
by this so-called
government employee.

00:54:57.590 --> 00:55:01.100 align:middle line:84%
And he wanted to know
how that had happened.

00:55:01.100 --> 00:55:04.310 align:middle line:84%
>> Jerry Ford called for the
long sought after congressional

00:55:04.310 --> 00:55:06.500 align:middle line:90%
hearing into UFOs.

00:55:06.500 --> 00:55:09.380 align:middle line:84%
It took place over one day
in front of the House Armed

00:55:09.380 --> 00:55:11.690 align:middle line:90%
Services Committee.

00:55:11.690 --> 00:55:14.330 align:middle line:84%
Highly embarrassed with
the stigma of swamp gas,

00:55:14.330 --> 00:55:16.400 align:middle line:84%
Allen Hynek joined
those calling for

00:55:16.400 --> 00:55:19.910 align:middle line:84%
an independent scientific
study of the problem.

00:55:19.910 --> 00:55:22.060 align:middle line:84%
The Air Force readily
agreed and offered

00:55:22.060 --> 00:55:23.920 align:middle line:84%
to fund it, which
probably should

00:55:23.920 --> 00:55:26.570 align:middle line:90%
have raised a cautionary flag.

00:55:26.570 --> 00:55:28.930 align:middle line:10%
But among the civilian
investigation groups,

00:55:28.930 --> 00:55:30.560 align:middle line:10%
there was euphoria.

00:55:30.560 --> 00:55:32.020 align:middle line:84%
It appeared there
would finally be

00:55:32.020 --> 00:55:34.170 align:middle line:90%
an independent scientific study.

00:55:34.170 --> 00:55:37.510 align:middle line:90%


00:55:37.510 --> 00:55:41.110 align:middle line:84%
In the wake of the
1966 swamp gas fiasco,

00:55:41.110 --> 00:55:44.170 align:middle line:84%
the Air Force approached a
number of A-list universities

00:55:44.170 --> 00:55:48.010 align:middle line:84%
to conduct a serious
scientific study of UFOs

00:55:48.010 --> 00:55:50.050 align:middle line:90%
and was turned down flat.

00:55:50.050 --> 00:55:52.030 align:middle line:10%
Finally, the
University of Colorado,

00:55:52.030 --> 00:55:55.960 align:middle line:10%
running low on federal grant
money, considered accepting.

00:55:55.960 --> 00:55:59.290 align:middle line:84%
Heading the study would be
the respected physicist Edward

00:55:59.290 --> 00:56:01.740 align:middle line:90%
Condon.

00:56:01.740 --> 00:56:05.310 align:middle line:84%
>> Edward Condon didn't want
do this for the Air Force,

00:56:05.310 --> 00:56:07.980 align:middle line:84%
even though he'd done a lot
of military consultancy work

00:56:07.980 --> 00:56:11.710 align:middle line:84%
before because he was like most
other people in the scientific

00:56:11.710 --> 00:56:12.510 align:middle line:90%
community.

00:56:12.510 --> 00:56:15.780 align:middle line:84%
He thought the whole thing was
nonsense, not worth his time.

00:56:15.780 --> 00:56:20.550 align:middle line:84%
But University of Colorado
needed some money.

00:56:20.550 --> 00:56:23.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Robert Lowe, the person who
would administer the project,

00:56:23.700 --> 00:56:27.690 align:middle line:84%
pitched it to one of the
university trustees thusly.

00:56:27.690 --> 00:56:29.310 align:middle line:84%
The trick would
be, to the public,

00:56:29.310 --> 00:56:31.770 align:middle line:84%
it would appear a
totally objective study.

00:56:31.770 --> 00:56:33.660 align:middle line:84%
But to the scientific
community, it

00:56:33.660 --> 00:56:36.930 align:middle line:84%
would present the image
of a group of nonbelievers

00:56:36.930 --> 00:56:38.910 align:middle line:84%
trying to be
objective but having

00:56:38.910 --> 00:56:43.390 align:middle line:84%
an almost zero expectation
of finding a saucer.

00:56:43.390 --> 00:56:46.200 align:middle line:84%
>> And that was Bob Lowe,
the used car salesman,

00:56:46.200 --> 00:56:49.650 align:middle line:84%
saying what he had to to the
board of trustees to relax

00:56:49.650 --> 00:56:54.120 align:middle line:84%
them, so they could put their
imprimatur on the project.

00:56:54.120 --> 00:56:56.880 align:middle line:84%
>> When discovered later, the
memo would have disastrous

00:56:56.880 --> 00:57:00.780 align:middle line:84%
consequences and convinced
the civilian research groups

00:57:00.780 --> 00:57:04.170 align:middle line:84%
who'd enthusiastically
cooperated up to that point

00:57:04.170 --> 00:57:06.480 align:middle line:90%
that a fix was in.

00:57:06.480 --> 00:57:09.570 align:middle line:84%
It turned out they were right
but not because of the Lowe

00:57:09.570 --> 00:57:11.180 align:middle line:90%
memo.

00:57:11.180 --> 00:57:13.040 align:middle line:84%
As the study was
getting underway,

00:57:13.040 --> 00:57:16.760 align:middle line:84%
Condon and Lowe met with
their Air Force liaison.

00:57:16.760 --> 00:57:19.160 align:middle line:84%
And incredibly, they
asked him what result

00:57:19.160 --> 00:57:21.020 align:middle line:90%
the Air Force would like.

00:57:21.020 --> 00:57:23.330 align:middle line:84%
The leaders of what's
supposed to be an inquiry

00:57:23.330 --> 00:57:28.160 align:middle line:84%
into the reality of UFOs asking
for direction from the agency

00:57:28.160 --> 00:57:30.710 align:middle line:84%
who'd been proclaiming
for two decades

00:57:30.710 --> 00:57:35.420 align:middle line:84%
that there was absolutely no
reality to them whatsoever.

00:57:35.420 --> 00:57:37.970 align:middle line:84%
The liaison officer
replied that the Air Force

00:57:37.970 --> 00:57:40.910 align:middle line:84%
was tired of funding
project Blue Book.

00:57:40.910 --> 00:57:43.520 align:middle line:84%
>> And what he
says to Condon is,

00:57:43.520 --> 00:57:46.760 align:middle line:84%
this project has been a source
of a lot of irritation really

00:57:46.760 --> 00:57:50.040 align:middle line:84%
to the Air Force and
a lot of expanse.

00:57:50.040 --> 00:57:53.580 align:middle line:84%
And we really need
to get rid of this.

00:57:53.580 --> 00:57:57.630 align:middle line:84%
And if you find that you
don't have enough money

00:57:57.630 --> 00:58:02.370 align:middle line:84%
to come to a proper
conclusion, reapply,

00:58:02.370 --> 00:58:03.600 align:middle line:90%
and you'll get more money.

00:58:03.600 --> 00:58:06.250 align:middle line:90%


00:58:06.250 --> 00:58:08.670 align:middle line:84%
>> The Colorado study brought
onboard a team of eight

00:58:08.670 --> 00:58:11.970 align:middle line:84%
scientists, engineers,
and psychologists.

00:58:11.970 --> 00:58:15.570 align:middle line:84%
Alan Hynek consulted
as did Keyhoe and NICAP

00:58:15.570 --> 00:58:18.240 align:middle line:84%
and an atmospheric physicist
from the University

00:58:18.240 --> 00:58:21.450 align:middle line:90%
of Arizona, Dr. James McDonald.

00:58:21.450 --> 00:58:25.830 align:middle line:84%
>> In 1954, he had a UFO
sighting in what we would call

00:58:25.830 --> 00:58:26.910 align:middle line:90%
a daylight disk.

00:58:26.910 --> 00:58:28.770 align:middle line:84%
And it was really a
very puzzling sighting,

00:58:28.770 --> 00:58:32.880 align:middle line:84%
a good sighting, obviously
a very good trained witness.

00:58:32.880 --> 00:58:34.990 align:middle line:84%
But he didn't do
anything with it,

00:58:34.990 --> 00:58:38.760 align:middle line:84%
because he was starting
his scientific career.

00:58:38.760 --> 00:58:41.220 align:middle line:10%
>> In the mid '60s,
McDonald picked up the study

00:58:41.220 --> 00:58:43.290 align:middle line:10%
of the phenomenon
with a vengeance,

00:58:43.290 --> 00:58:46.020 align:middle line:10%
reading through all the Blue
Book files and the extensive

00:58:46.020 --> 00:58:47.850 align:middle line:10%
public literature.

00:58:47.850 --> 00:58:50.340 align:middle line:84%
>> He went through all of
this in a period of months,

00:58:50.340 --> 00:58:55.230 align:middle line:84%
began talking with witnesses,
was really impressed with

00:58:55.230 --> 00:58:56.250 align:middle line:90%
the quality of evidence.

00:58:56.250 --> 00:58:58.710 align:middle line:84%
And he thought that this
was the most important

00:58:58.710 --> 00:59:01.680 align:middle line:84%
overlooked scientific
question of the century, maybe

00:59:01.680 --> 00:59:04.220 align:middle line:84%
one of the most important
of the millennium.

00:59:04.220 --> 00:59:08.190 align:middle line:84%
>> McDonal was fearless,
vocal, and tireless.

00:59:08.190 --> 00:59:10.470 align:middle line:84%
>> He began giving
hundreds of talks.

00:59:10.470 --> 00:59:12.810 align:middle line:90%
And I mean hundreds of talks.

00:59:12.810 --> 00:59:17.040 align:middle line:10%
And a lot of scientists in
these prestigious organizations

00:59:17.040 --> 00:59:22.110 align:middle line:10%
began to take an open interest
in the subject of UFOs.

00:59:22.110 --> 00:59:25.020 align:middle line:10%
>> But even as McDonald was
raising awareness in the wider

00:59:25.020 --> 00:59:28.800 align:middle line:10%
scientific community, the
Colorado study researchers were

00:59:28.800 --> 00:59:32.940 align:middle line:10%
learning how unusually unaware
Edward Condon appeared to be.

00:59:32.940 --> 00:59:36.360 align:middle line:10%
>> He couldn't understand why
people were so upset that he

00:59:36.360 --> 00:59:39.970 align:middle line:10%
had talked about trying to
debunk the UFO phenomenon.

00:59:39.970 --> 00:59:42.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, to most
people, that sounds

00:59:42.210 --> 00:59:45.540 align:middle line:84%
like somebody that's
already got his mind made up

00:59:45.540 --> 00:59:47.700 align:middle line:90%
and how can we discredit it.

00:59:47.700 --> 00:59:49.770 align:middle line:84%
>> Still hoping for
an objective study,

00:59:49.770 --> 00:59:53.490 align:middle line:84%
the Colorado researchers went
into the field to investigate

00:59:53.490 --> 00:59:57.480 align:middle line:84%
both old classic incidents and
some new ones as they cropped

00:59:57.480 --> 01:00:00.450 align:middle line:84%
up during the
course of the study.

01:00:00.450 --> 01:00:03.870 align:middle line:10%
One such case was the Falcon
Lake Manitoba incident,

01:00:03.870 --> 01:00:07.320 align:middle line:10%
where a weekend prospector
named Stefan Michalak told

01:00:07.320 --> 01:00:10.440 align:middle line:10%
of how he had approached
a landed disk thinking

01:00:10.440 --> 01:00:13.020 align:middle line:10%
it was an American
test craft in trouble.

01:00:13.020 --> 01:00:14.700 align:middle line:10%
>> He saw two of them.

01:00:14.700 --> 01:00:18.780 align:middle line:84%
One stayed in the sky and
then headed off to the north.

01:00:18.780 --> 01:00:22.680 align:middle line:84%
And the other one landed over
there on that rock outcropping.

01:00:22.680 --> 01:00:27.810 align:middle line:84%
He progressed and walked up to
the door of this thing, which

01:00:27.810 --> 01:00:32.070 align:middle line:84%
was situated
somewhere about here,

01:00:32.070 --> 01:00:36.630 align:middle line:84%
and put his hand on
the side of the door,

01:00:36.630 --> 01:00:39.660 align:middle line:84%
and poked his head in, saw
that there were some flashing

01:00:39.660 --> 01:00:43.290 align:middle line:84%
lights like on a computer,
saw that his hand, his glove

01:00:43.290 --> 01:00:45.760 align:middle line:90%
was melted very, very hot.

01:00:45.760 --> 01:00:49.320 align:middle line:84%
And at this time, he had
already shouted in, come on,

01:00:49.320 --> 01:00:51.060 align:middle line:90%
Yankee boys, need some help?

01:00:51.060 --> 01:00:53.640 align:middle line:84%
Let me help you
fix your machine.

01:00:53.640 --> 01:00:55.450 align:middle line:90%
And the voices stopped.

01:00:55.450 --> 01:00:58.920 align:middle line:10%
At this point, the
doors on this thing

01:00:58.920 --> 01:01:02.400 align:middle line:10%
slid shut, kind of like an iris.

01:01:02.400 --> 01:01:05.430 align:middle line:84%
And the entire
object rotated, so

01:01:05.430 --> 01:01:08.070 align:middle line:84%
that there was a grille
or exhaust vent right

01:01:08.070 --> 01:01:09.690 align:middle line:90%
in front of him.

01:01:09.690 --> 01:01:13.620 align:middle line:84%
And as he stood right close
to it, a blast of hot gas

01:01:13.620 --> 01:01:17.850 align:middle line:84%
shot out, knocking
him down, and then

01:01:17.850 --> 01:01:19.650 align:middle line:84%
actually setting
some of his clothes

01:01:19.650 --> 01:01:22.800 align:middle line:90%
on fire with the intense heat.

01:01:22.800 --> 01:01:25.800 align:middle line:84%
And the object took
off, rose into the air.

01:01:25.800 --> 01:01:28.180 align:middle line:84%
And because he was
disoriented and distracted,

01:01:28.180 --> 01:01:30.720 align:middle line:84%
he couldn't tell which
direction it went.

01:01:30.720 --> 01:01:35.040 align:middle line:84%
But he spent some time rolling
on the ground putting out

01:01:35.040 --> 01:01:36.540 align:middle line:90%
his clothes, taking them off.

01:01:36.540 --> 01:01:39.250 align:middle line:90%


01:01:39.250 --> 01:01:42.490 align:middle line:84%
And then the ordeal of
getting back to civilization

01:01:42.490 --> 01:01:46.060 align:middle line:84%
began, because he was
feeling very nauseous,

01:01:46.060 --> 01:01:47.960 align:middle line:90%
very, very disoriented.

01:01:47.960 --> 01:01:51.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Michalak staggered out of the
bush and got back to Winnipeg

01:01:51.520 --> 01:01:53.030 align:middle line:90%
extremely sick.

01:01:53.030 --> 01:01:55.150 align:middle line:10%
And I remember going
into their bedroom.

01:01:55.150 --> 01:01:59.470 align:middle line:10%
And even before I stepped
in over the threshold,

01:01:59.470 --> 01:02:02.970 align:middle line:10%
the smell in the house and the
smell coming from the bedroom

01:02:02.970 --> 01:02:05.200 align:middle line:10%
was horrible.

01:02:05.200 --> 01:02:08.530 align:middle line:84%
But for days afterwards,
the smell lingered.

01:02:08.530 --> 01:02:11.290 align:middle line:84%
And the more I visited with
him, the more we chatted,

01:02:11.290 --> 01:02:15.580 align:middle line:84%
the more it felt as though the
smell was coming out of him,

01:02:15.580 --> 01:02:18.460 align:middle line:84%
that he was exuding this
stink, that it was pouring out

01:02:18.460 --> 01:02:19.330 align:middle line:90%
of his pores.

01:02:19.330 --> 01:02:22.900 align:middle line:10%
>> He also had some
fainting spells.

01:02:22.900 --> 01:02:25.870 align:middle line:10%
He had a recurring
skin condition

01:02:25.870 --> 01:02:28.540 align:middle line:10%
as a result and some
burning to his legs

01:02:28.540 --> 01:02:30.770 align:middle line:10%
too, because when
he fell backwards,

01:02:30.770 --> 01:02:33.760 align:middle line:10%
the blast also caught
him on the legs.

01:02:33.760 --> 01:02:37.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Two weeks later, Roy Craig,
a Colorado study chemist,

01:02:37.190 --> 01:02:39.880 align:middle line:84%
accompanied Michalak,
a "Life" photographer,

01:02:39.880 --> 01:02:44.070 align:middle line:84%
and Canadian authorities in
a journey out to the site.

01:02:44.070 --> 01:02:47.010 align:middle line:84%
They found it suspicious that
Michalak couldn't find the rock

01:02:47.010 --> 01:02:51.220 align:middle line:84%
outcrop where he claimed the
encounter had taken place.

01:02:51.220 --> 01:02:53.910 align:middle line:84%
There was also a forest
ranger tower a mile away,

01:02:53.910 --> 01:02:58.290 align:middle line:84%
and the ranger hadn't noticed
anything unusual in the air.

01:02:58.290 --> 01:03:00.960 align:middle line:84%
For these reasons, Roy
Craig dismissed the incident

01:03:00.960 --> 01:03:03.000 align:middle line:90%
as a hoax.

01:03:03.000 --> 01:03:04.710 align:middle line:84%
But in the following
months and years,

01:03:04.710 --> 01:03:06.690 align:middle line:84%
Michalak's health
suffered immensely

01:03:06.690 --> 01:03:09.690 align:middle line:90%
from no diagnosable cause.

01:03:09.690 --> 01:03:11.910 align:middle line:84%
That, and the
official skepticism,

01:03:11.910 --> 01:03:14.790 align:middle line:84%
affected him for the
remainder of his life.

01:03:14.790 --> 01:03:18.660 align:middle line:84%
>> What bothered him most
was being let down by all

01:03:18.660 --> 01:03:22.370 align:middle line:84%
of the people he turned to
and said, this happened to me.

01:03:22.370 --> 01:03:23.560 align:middle line:90%
Help me.

01:03:23.560 --> 01:03:25.110 align:middle line:90%
What is this?

01:03:25.110 --> 01:03:27.060 align:middle line:84%
Instead, he got,
well, we're not sure.

01:03:27.060 --> 01:03:28.710 align:middle line:84%
You burned yourself
on a barbecue.

01:03:28.710 --> 01:03:29.880 align:middle line:90%
Blah, blah, blah.

01:03:29.880 --> 01:03:31.590 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:03:31.590 --> 01:03:34.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Meanwhile, back at the
University of Colorado,

01:03:34.320 --> 01:03:37.800 align:middle line:84%
Condon was spending little
time with the project.

01:03:37.800 --> 01:03:40.020 align:middle line:84%
Instead of doing any
field investigation,

01:03:40.020 --> 01:03:43.080 align:middle line:84%
he was enjoying the
company of contactees

01:03:43.080 --> 01:03:45.210 align:middle line:84%
and regaling his
professional colleagues

01:03:45.210 --> 01:03:47.310 align:middle line:90%
with their absurd tales.

01:03:47.310 --> 01:03:51.060 align:middle line:84%
When Jim McDonald gave a
seminar in the summer of '67,

01:03:51.060 --> 01:03:54.660 align:middle line:90%
Condon fell asleep twice.

01:03:54.660 --> 01:03:58.020 align:middle line:84%
That same summer, Roy Craig
happened upon Lowe's trick memo

01:03:58.020 --> 01:04:01.050 align:middle line:84%
in the files, the one written
to sell the university

01:04:01.050 --> 01:04:03.520 align:middle line:90%
trustees on the project.

01:04:03.520 --> 01:04:06.330 align:middle line:84%
Disturbed, Craig showed it
to Norman Levine and David

01:04:06.330 --> 01:04:08.970 align:middle line:84%
Saunders, two of
the project's staff

01:04:08.970 --> 01:04:12.510 align:middle line:84%
who were most bothered
by Condon's behavior.

01:04:12.510 --> 01:04:14.190 align:middle line:84%
Saunders showed
it to Keyhoe, who

01:04:14.190 --> 01:04:17.400 align:middle line:84%
gave it to Jim McDonald, who
mentioned it in a long letter

01:04:17.400 --> 01:04:20.670 align:middle line:84%
to Lowe about the negative
direction the project seemed

01:04:20.670 --> 01:04:22.260 align:middle line:90%
to be taking.

01:04:22.260 --> 01:04:24.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Bob Lowe was very,
very worried about this.

01:04:24.780 --> 01:04:30.150 align:middle line:84%
But Ed Condon, typically of
him, was explosive about it.

01:04:30.150 --> 01:04:32.640 align:middle line:84%
He considered this
to be an issue

01:04:32.640 --> 01:04:35.310 align:middle line:84%
of betrayal on the
part of what should

01:04:35.310 --> 01:04:38.220 align:middle line:90%
be a private in-house team.

01:04:38.220 --> 01:04:41.130 align:middle line:84%
And he called David Saunders
and Norman Levine in,

01:04:41.130 --> 01:04:43.070 align:middle line:90%
and he just fired them.

01:04:43.070 --> 01:04:47.220 align:middle line:84%
And he not only fired them, but
he told them that if he could,

01:04:47.220 --> 01:04:50.850 align:middle line:84%
he would ruin their
academic careers over this.

01:04:50.850 --> 01:04:54.210 align:middle line:84%
>> As threats of suits and
counter-suits filled the air,

01:04:54.210 --> 01:04:56.880 align:middle line:84%
Lowe's assistant
administrator resigned,

01:04:56.880 --> 01:05:00.120 align:middle line:84%
citing an almost unanimous
lack of confidence in his

01:05:00.120 --> 01:05:01.980 align:middle line:90%
objectivity.

01:05:01.980 --> 01:05:05.130 align:middle line:84%
>> All these people are falling
out of this so-called objective

01:05:05.130 --> 01:05:06.240 align:middle line:90%
scientific project.

01:05:06.240 --> 01:05:08.220 align:middle line:90%
They're dropping like flies.

01:05:08.220 --> 01:05:12.720 align:middle line:84%
And what you have left over
is Ed Condon, and Roy Craig,

01:05:12.720 --> 01:05:14.760 align:middle line:84%
and a bunch of other
people who've basically

01:05:14.760 --> 01:05:17.580 align:middle line:84%
been added on at the
last second, trying

01:05:17.580 --> 01:05:20.640 align:middle line:84%
to cobble together a
mishmash of documents

01:05:20.640 --> 01:05:23.670 align:middle line:84%
that they called the
scientific study of UFOs.

01:05:23.670 --> 01:05:26.670 align:middle line:84%
Well, it was a
terrible piece of work.

01:05:26.670 --> 01:05:29.700 align:middle line:84%
>> The report was immediately
hailed by "The New York Times"

01:05:29.700 --> 01:05:32.970 align:middle line:84%
science reporter, who had
turned out had already written

01:05:32.970 --> 01:05:36.960 align:middle line:84%
a laudatory introduction
to the paperback edition.

01:05:36.960 --> 01:05:41.310 align:middle line:84%
Its 1,485 pages were
prefaced by Condon's 50 pages

01:05:41.310 --> 01:05:44.070 align:middle line:84%
of negative
conclusions, conclusions

01:05:44.070 --> 01:05:47.100 align:middle line:84%
that dismissed or ignored
much of the analysis

01:05:47.100 --> 01:05:49.290 align:middle line:90%
in the body of the report.

01:05:49.290 --> 01:05:52.440 align:middle line:84%
Bill Hartman, extremely
skeptical about UFOs,

01:05:52.440 --> 01:05:55.830 align:middle line:84%
had nevertheless concluded
about the Trent pictures

01:05:55.830 --> 01:05:59.370 align:middle line:84%
that all factors appear to be
consistent with the assertion

01:05:59.370 --> 01:06:01.770 align:middle line:84%
that an extraordinary
flying object flew

01:06:01.770 --> 01:06:03.550 align:middle line:84%
within the sight
of two witnesses.

01:06:03.550 --> 01:06:05.890 align:middle line:84%
>> He, in his conclusions,
completely ignores--

01:06:05.890 --> 01:06:06.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:06:06.690 --> 01:06:08.023 align:middle line:90%
>> --ignores talking about that.

01:06:08.023 --> 01:06:10.630 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, infers the
opposite, no question.

01:06:10.630 --> 01:06:11.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, yeah.

01:06:11.430 --> 01:06:12.900 align:middle line:90%
I think infers the opposite is--

01:06:12.900 --> 01:06:13.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Infers the opposite--

01:06:13.980 --> 01:06:16.920 align:middle line:90%
>> --fair.

01:06:16.920 --> 01:06:22.130 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, I don't know
quite what to say.

01:06:22.130 --> 01:06:26.100 align:middle line:84%
I think what you're
saying is basically right.

01:06:26.100 --> 01:06:28.140 align:middle line:84%
Whether those
conclusions should have

01:06:28.140 --> 01:06:30.030 align:middle line:84%
been written
totally differently,

01:06:30.030 --> 01:06:32.160 align:middle line:84%
I suspect they
should have been--

01:06:32.160 --> 01:06:34.170 align:middle line:84%
you don't write those
things without sort

01:06:34.170 --> 01:06:36.060 align:middle line:84%
of knowing what the
consequences are going

01:06:36.060 --> 01:06:37.890 align:middle line:90%
to be for people at his level.

01:06:37.890 --> 01:06:38.880 align:middle line:90%
And I don't know.

01:06:38.880 --> 01:06:43.710 align:middle line:84%
Maybe he's just more,
even more deviously canny

01:06:43.710 --> 01:06:44.700 align:middle line:90%
than I'm saying.

01:06:44.700 --> 01:06:47.160 align:middle line:84%
Because maybe he just figures,
well, if I, Edward Condon,

01:06:47.160 --> 01:06:48.960 align:middle line:84%
say there's nothing
here in this report,

01:06:48.960 --> 01:06:51.900 align:middle line:84%
nobody will bother
to go further.

01:06:51.900 --> 01:06:55.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Both McDonald and Allen
Hynek fought tenaciously against

01:06:55.140 --> 01:06:57.660 align:middle line:84%
the acceptance of Condon's
conclusions within

01:06:57.660 --> 01:07:01.950 align:middle line:84%
the scientific community,
but it was a losing battle.

01:07:01.950 --> 01:07:03.660 align:middle line:84%
The Air Force shut
down Blue Book,

01:07:03.660 --> 01:07:08.160 align:middle line:84%
and Keyhoe's NICAP went into
a steep membership decline.

01:07:08.160 --> 01:07:11.550 align:middle line:84%
McDonald sunk into a depression
from marital problems

01:07:11.550 --> 01:07:14.290 align:middle line:84%
and would soon
take his own life.

01:07:14.290 --> 01:07:15.930 align:middle line:10%
Hynek Nick soldiered
on, founding

01:07:15.930 --> 01:07:18.330 align:middle line:10%
the Center for UFO Studies.

01:07:18.330 --> 01:07:21.240 align:middle line:10%
But the ground was shifting
in a fundamental way.

01:07:21.240 --> 01:07:23.970 align:middle line:84%
>> As proof of the
extraterrestrial hypothesis

01:07:23.970 --> 01:07:29.460 align:middle line:84%
remained elusive, some
ufologists began to look

01:07:29.460 --> 01:07:30.540 align:middle line:90%
in other directions.

01:07:30.540 --> 01:07:33.050 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:07:33.050 --> 01:07:35.600 align:middle line:84%
>> As the late '60s saw
the planet as a whole,

01:07:35.600 --> 01:07:38.180 align:middle line:84%
undivided by
artificial boundaries,

01:07:38.180 --> 01:07:41.480 align:middle line:84%
the decade had also brought into
the culture the Eastern notion

01:07:41.480 --> 01:07:43.820 align:middle line:90%
of expanded consciousness.

01:07:43.820 --> 01:07:47.240 align:middle line:84%
And tagging along, its
frequent fellow travelers--

01:07:47.240 --> 01:07:50.390 align:middle line:90%
the paranormal and the occult.

01:07:50.390 --> 01:07:53.570 align:middle line:84%
>> In 1969, Jacques Valle
wrote a book called "Passport

01:07:53.570 --> 01:07:57.890 align:middle line:84%
to Magonia," where he links
modern UFOs to traditional

01:07:57.890 --> 01:08:02.390 align:middle line:84%
beliefs about
fairies, demons, gods,

01:08:02.390 --> 01:08:04.860 align:middle line:90%
entities of various kinds.

01:08:04.860 --> 01:08:07.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Jacques Valle had been
one of Allen Hynek's graduate

01:08:07.500 --> 01:08:09.030 align:middle line:90%
astronomy students.

01:08:09.030 --> 01:08:11.400 align:middle line:84%
And Valle's influence had
been one of the reasons

01:08:11.400 --> 01:08:15.060 align:middle line:84%
for Hynek's change
of heart on UFOs.

01:08:15.060 --> 01:08:18.090 align:middle line:84%
In his new book, Valle pointed
out that the reports of fairy

01:08:18.090 --> 01:08:22.439 align:middle line:84%
encounters of yore and modern
UFO occupant reports had many

01:08:22.439 --> 01:08:25.920 align:middle line:90%
qualities in common.

01:08:25.920 --> 01:08:28.859 align:middle line:84%
In Europe, many researchers
embraced this idea,

01:08:28.859 --> 01:08:33.240 align:middle line:84%
that a UFOs were the modern
face of an old phenomenon, one

01:08:33.240 --> 01:08:38.790 align:middle line:84%
that was psychosocial in
nature, not extraterrestrial.

01:08:38.790 --> 01:08:42.210 align:middle line:84%
>> The whole premise was
that these things couldn't be

01:08:42.210 --> 01:08:43.380 align:middle line:90%
happening.

01:08:43.380 --> 01:08:44.430 align:middle line:90%
This was implicit.

01:08:44.430 --> 01:08:49.200 align:middle line:84%
It was really the
debunking view by another,

01:08:49.200 --> 01:08:51.300 align:middle line:90%
more pretentious name.

01:08:51.300 --> 01:08:53.220 align:middle line:84%
And so there was
this great effort

01:08:53.220 --> 01:08:57.330 align:middle line:84%
to study the most extreme
kinds of experiential claims,

01:08:57.330 --> 01:09:01.649 align:middle line:84%
and without really much
empirical investigation

01:09:01.649 --> 01:09:05.200 align:middle line:84%
or documentation, just
claiming that by their nature,

01:09:05.200 --> 01:09:10.109 align:middle line:84%
they were explainable as
the witnesses' deep-seated

01:09:10.109 --> 01:09:13.930 align:middle line:84%
psychological or spiritual
needs, often ascribed

01:09:13.930 --> 01:09:16.470 align:middle line:84%
to witnesses that the
writers had never met

01:09:16.470 --> 01:09:19.377 align:middle line:84%
and knew nothing about,
except what they had reported.

01:09:19.377 --> 01:09:20.784 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:09:20.784 --> 01:09:22.660 align:middle line:90%
[HELICOPTER BLADES]

01:09:22.660 --> 01:09:25.840 align:middle line:84%
>> As if to offset all
this armchair theorizing,

01:09:25.840 --> 01:09:30.010 align:middle line:90%
1973 saw a massive UFO wave.

01:09:30.010 --> 01:09:33.640 align:middle line:84%
In one spectacular episode,
four Ohio National Guardsmen

01:09:33.640 --> 01:09:36.040 align:middle line:84%
reported narrowly
averting a collision

01:09:36.040 --> 01:09:39.220 align:middle line:84%
with an object that stopped
for a few seconds above.

01:09:39.220 --> 01:09:41.276 align:middle line:10%
>> It was so close
to us, at that time,

01:09:41.276 --> 01:09:43.359 align:middle line:10%
I was concerned that we
might have a blade strike,

01:09:43.359 --> 01:09:47.080 align:middle line:10%
because I could see the tips of
the rotor blades reflecting off

01:09:47.080 --> 01:09:48.279 align:middle line:10%
the light.

01:09:48.279 --> 01:09:50.380 align:middle line:90%
And it was awful close to that.

01:09:50.380 --> 01:09:52.850 align:middle line:84%
And it was, as I say,
this big thing in front--

01:09:52.850 --> 01:09:54.628 align:middle line:84%
big, black solid thing,
because the stars

01:09:54.628 --> 01:09:55.670 align:middle line:90%
were gone in front of us.

01:09:55.670 --> 01:09:56.470 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

01:09:56.470 --> 01:09:59.350 align:middle line:84%
I'm guessing 80, 80
feet, maybe, long.

01:09:59.350 --> 01:10:01.800 align:middle line:84%
>> What were you thinking
when you looked at it?

01:10:01.800 --> 01:10:03.330 align:middle line:90%
>> I was awestruck.

01:10:03.330 --> 01:10:07.320 align:middle line:84%
>> The entire event was observed
by a family on the ground

01:10:07.320 --> 01:10:10.890 align:middle line:84%
Philip J. Klass, an aviation
journalist and the arch UFO

01:10:10.890 --> 01:10:14.040 align:middle line:84%
skeptic now that Donald
Menzel had retired,

01:10:14.040 --> 01:10:17.190 align:middle line:84%
explained that what the
guardsman saw was a slow-moving

01:10:17.190 --> 01:10:18.042 align:middle line:90%
meteor.

01:10:18.042 --> 01:10:19.250 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

01:10:19.250 --> 01:10:20.820 align:middle line:90%
>> That's worse than swamp gas.

01:10:20.820 --> 01:10:21.135 align:middle line:90%
>> That is.

01:10:21.135 --> 01:10:21.750 align:middle line:90%
That is awful.

01:10:21.750 --> 01:10:22.890 align:middle line:90%
>> That's worse than swamp gas.

01:10:22.890 --> 01:10:23.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yes.

01:10:23.790 --> 01:10:28.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Therefore, I shall resign the
presidency, effective at noon.

01:10:28.590 --> 01:10:30.870 align:middle line:84%
>> But as the times
grew in uncertainty,

01:10:30.870 --> 01:10:33.840 align:middle line:84%
so it seemed did the will to
believe in cause and effect

01:10:33.840 --> 01:10:38.620 align:middle line:84%
connections that strain facts,
especially archaeological ones.

01:10:38.620 --> 01:10:41.738 align:middle line:84%
>> [INAUDIBLE] didn't
know about astronauts.

01:10:41.738 --> 01:10:42.714 align:middle line:90%
But we do.

01:10:42.714 --> 01:10:45.160 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:10:45.160 --> 01:10:48.430 align:middle line:84%
>> The 1974 documentary
"Chariots of the Gods"

01:10:48.430 --> 01:10:51.280 align:middle line:84%
popularized the notion
that the mysterious wonders

01:10:51.280 --> 01:10:54.340 align:middle line:84%
of the ancient world were
attributable to alien

01:10:54.340 --> 01:10:55.810 align:middle line:90%
astronauts.

01:10:55.810 --> 01:10:58.270 align:middle line:90%
The film grossed $25 million.

01:10:58.270 --> 01:11:01.510 align:middle line:84%
>> The giant drawings must have
been made for someone arriving

01:11:01.510 --> 01:11:02.320 align:middle line:90%
by air.

01:11:02.320 --> 01:11:05.500 align:middle line:84%
>> But if extraterrestrials have
made contact with our primitive

01:11:05.500 --> 01:11:09.310 align:middle line:84%
ancestors, they remain
stubbornly aloof from us,

01:11:09.310 --> 01:11:12.550 align:middle line:84%
except apparently
in rare incidents--

01:11:12.550 --> 01:11:15.820 align:middle line:84%
one in particular that revealed
that a face to face encounter

01:11:15.820 --> 01:11:18.820 align:middle line:84%
with an advanced
non-human intelligence

01:11:18.820 --> 01:11:23.760 align:middle line:84%
might have profoundly
disturbing undercurrents.

01:11:23.760 --> 01:11:28.650 align:middle line:84%
Toward the end of 1975, in the
forests of northern Arizona,

01:11:28.650 --> 01:11:30.660 align:middle line:84%
a truck carrying
home six loggers

01:11:30.660 --> 01:11:34.710 align:middle line:84%
stopped when they noticed a
glowing object in a clearing.

01:11:34.710 --> 01:11:39.680 align:middle line:84%
Travis Walton jumped out
and walked towards it.

01:11:39.680 --> 01:11:42.380 align:middle line:84%
His friends told the police
that they took off in fright

01:11:42.380 --> 01:11:46.400 align:middle line:84%
when they saw him knocked
flying by a bright blue flash,

01:11:46.400 --> 01:11:49.880 align:middle line:84%
and that when they returned
15 minutes later, he was gone,

01:11:49.880 --> 01:11:52.190 align:middle line:90%
and so was the object.

01:11:52.190 --> 01:11:55.010 align:middle line:84%
Five days later, a shaken
and dazed Travis Walton

01:11:55.010 --> 01:11:57.440 align:middle line:90%
called from a roadside phone.

01:11:57.440 --> 01:12:00.200 align:middle line:84%
He didn't remember much
about what happened,

01:12:00.200 --> 01:12:02.630 align:middle line:84%
but he would never forget
the moments after he

01:12:02.630 --> 01:12:04.220 align:middle line:90%
regained consciousness.

01:12:04.220 --> 01:12:06.980 align:middle line:10%
>> I was in a lot of pain,
and I didn't remember what had

01:12:06.980 --> 01:12:08.420 align:middle line:10%
happened at first.

01:12:08.420 --> 01:12:11.150 align:middle line:10%
But then that kind
of came back to me.

01:12:11.150 --> 01:12:13.520 align:middle line:84%
But I still didn't put it
together with where I was.

01:12:13.520 --> 01:12:15.680 align:middle line:84%
I was thinking
that I'd been hurt,

01:12:15.680 --> 01:12:18.200 align:middle line:84%
and they'd taken
me to a hospital

01:12:18.200 --> 01:12:24.780 align:middle line:84%
and that's where I was, that the
sounds of movement around me,

01:12:24.780 --> 01:12:28.340 align:middle line:84%
that these were doctors, and
things were under control.

01:12:28.340 --> 01:12:31.190 align:middle line:90%


01:12:31.190 --> 01:12:34.430 align:middle line:84%
There was some sort of a device
pressing down on my chest.

01:12:34.430 --> 01:12:36.830 align:middle line:84%
And all of the
pain and everything

01:12:36.830 --> 01:12:38.750 align:middle line:84%
made me feel like
I just better stay

01:12:38.750 --> 01:12:41.810 align:middle line:84%
still because that's what
you do in a situation

01:12:41.810 --> 01:12:43.910 align:middle line:90%
when you're being treated.

01:12:43.910 --> 01:12:47.690 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think I
was being treated.

01:12:47.690 --> 01:12:52.550 align:middle line:84%
When I finally could focus
my eyes, and saw where I was,

01:12:52.550 --> 01:12:55.760 align:middle line:84%
and saw these creatures--
just to look into the eyes

01:12:55.760 --> 01:13:04.820 align:middle line:84%
of something, a thinking
creature that wasn't human--

01:13:04.820 --> 01:13:07.940 align:middle line:90%
it was a shock.

01:13:07.940 --> 01:13:11.219 align:middle line:84%
That instant is something
that'll never, never leave me.

01:13:11.219 --> 01:13:18.330 align:middle line:90%


01:13:18.330 --> 01:13:20.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Steven Spielberg gave
an interview when he was

01:13:20.820 --> 01:13:23.820 align:middle line:84%
in pre-production on "Close
Encounters of the Third Kind."

01:13:23.820 --> 01:13:26.520 align:middle line:90%


01:13:26.520 --> 01:13:29.220 align:middle line:84%
He talked about one night
driving out to the desert,

01:13:29.220 --> 01:13:31.050 align:middle line:84%
staring at the
sky, and wondering,

01:13:31.050 --> 01:13:35.460 align:middle line:84%
if a UFO came down and
landed, would he get aboard?

01:13:35.460 --> 01:13:37.710 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, he got
very frightened.

01:13:37.710 --> 01:13:39.900 align:middle line:84%
He jumped in his car
and drove back to LA.

01:13:39.900 --> 01:13:45.480 align:middle line:90%


01:13:45.480 --> 01:13:47.340 align:middle line:84%
"Close Encounters
of the Third Kind"

01:13:47.340 --> 01:13:51.510 align:middle line:90%
was the first great UFO film.

01:13:51.510 --> 01:13:54.050 align:middle line:84%
But in the actual
landing scene, the humans

01:13:54.050 --> 01:13:56.370 align:middle line:84%
are struck not with
fear, but with awe.

01:13:56.370 --> 01:13:57.170 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:13:57.170 --> 01:13:58.580 align:middle line:90%
The aliens are angelic.

01:13:58.580 --> 01:14:05.650 align:middle line:90%


01:14:05.650 --> 01:14:08.810 align:middle line:84%
The film's release marked
another turning point.

01:14:08.810 --> 01:14:11.710 align:middle line:84%
UFOs, the rejected
child of science,

01:14:11.710 --> 01:14:15.240 align:middle line:84%
had passed out of the realm
of mainstream culture.

01:14:15.240 --> 01:14:19.260 align:middle line:84%
It was now the province of
pop culture and its myths.

01:14:19.260 --> 01:14:22.410 align:middle line:84%
And of its myths, the film's
culminating contact scene

01:14:22.410 --> 01:14:24.870 align:middle line:90%
was foretelling.

01:14:24.870 --> 01:14:27.130 align:middle line:84%
During the first three
decades of the phenomenon,

01:14:27.130 --> 01:14:31.450 align:middle line:84%
there had been no attempt by our
apparent visitors to say hello.

01:14:31.450 --> 01:14:35.530 align:middle line:84%
The mythic unconscious, like
nature, abhors a vacuum.

01:14:35.530 --> 01:14:38.290 align:middle line:84%
And the notion of contact
would dominate the last three

01:14:38.290 --> 01:14:40.010 align:middle line:90%
decades.

01:14:40.010 --> 01:14:43.690 align:middle line:84%
But if the Spielberg version
was all sweetness and light,

01:14:43.690 --> 01:14:46.669 align:middle line:84%
the dark side was just
around the corner.

01:14:46.669 --> 01:14:54.410 align:middle line:90%


01:14:54.410 --> 01:14:57.980 align:middle line:10%
By the late '70s, requests
made under the new US Freedom

01:14:57.980 --> 01:15:01.340 align:middle line:10%
of Information Act were
revealing a fascinating series

01:15:01.340 --> 01:15:03.530 align:middle line:10%
of incidents at
Minuteman missile bases

01:15:03.530 --> 01:15:06.800 align:middle line:10%
along the US-Canada
border, and showing

01:15:06.800 --> 01:15:08.900 align:middle line:10%
that despite the end
of Project Blue Book,

01:15:08.900 --> 01:15:11.060 align:middle line:10%
the Air Force continued
to investigate

01:15:11.060 --> 01:15:14.090 align:middle line:10%
UFO reports involving its
personnel and facilities.

01:15:14.090 --> 01:15:17.050 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:15:17.050 --> 01:15:17.850 align:middle line:90%


01:15:17.850 --> 01:15:20.460 align:middle line:84%
It was a period of flux,
when the modern history

01:15:20.460 --> 01:15:24.940 align:middle line:84%
of the phenomenon was about to
make a radical course change.

01:15:24.940 --> 01:15:27.150 align:middle line:84%
A fateful moment
arrived as a tip

01:15:27.150 --> 01:15:29.407 align:middle line:84%
from a television
station manager.

01:15:29.407 --> 01:15:30.990 align:middle line:10%
>> Out of the blue,
he says, you know,

01:15:30.990 --> 01:15:33.380 align:middle line:10%
the guy you ought to
talk to is Jesse Marcel.

01:15:33.380 --> 01:15:36.270 align:middle line:10%
And brilliant investigator
that I am, I said, who's he?

01:15:36.270 --> 01:15:38.677 align:middle line:84%
And he says, oh, he
handled the wreckage of one

01:15:38.677 --> 01:15:40.260 align:middle line:84%
of those saucers
you're interested in.

01:15:40.260 --> 01:15:41.760 align:middle line:90%
He was in the military.

01:15:41.760 --> 01:15:43.860 align:middle line:90%
What?

01:15:43.860 --> 01:15:46.380 align:middle line:10%
>> The events related
by Major Jesse Marcel,

01:15:46.380 --> 01:15:50.700 align:middle line:10%
retired former intelligence
officer of the 509th atomic

01:15:50.700 --> 01:15:53.370 align:middle line:10%
bomb wing at
Roswell, New Mexico,

01:15:53.370 --> 01:15:56.970 align:middle line:10%
would provide the seed for a
crashed saucer story that would

01:15:56.970 --> 01:16:00.660 align:middle line:10%
take root and grow like an
enormous weed to overrun

01:16:00.660 --> 01:16:03.210 align:middle line:10%
the UFO landscape.

01:16:03.210 --> 01:16:06.270 align:middle line:84%
Witnesses were discovered who
reported a massive recovery

01:16:06.270 --> 01:16:07.530 align:middle line:90%
operation.

01:16:07.530 --> 01:16:10.080 align:middle line:10%
More witnesses came
forward, claiming

01:16:10.080 --> 01:16:13.170 align:middle line:10%
they saw wreckage and bodies.

01:16:13.170 --> 01:16:15.490 align:middle line:10%
>> By 1980, we
talked to 62 people.

01:16:15.490 --> 01:16:19.290 align:middle line:10%
By '85, it was 92 people.

01:16:19.290 --> 01:16:21.990 align:middle line:10%
Around the same time, the
memo that Wilbert Smith

01:16:21.990 --> 01:16:25.290 align:middle line:10%
wrote to his superiors
in Ottawa back in 1950

01:16:25.290 --> 01:16:28.350 align:middle line:10%
was discovered in his
papers, the one reporting

01:16:28.350 --> 01:16:31.770 align:middle line:10%
on his conversation with Defense
Research Board scientist Dr.

01:16:31.770 --> 01:16:35.820 align:middle line:10%
Robert Sarbacher that a crashed
saucer was being analyzed

01:16:35.820 --> 01:16:39.060 align:middle line:10%
by a small group of top
level scientists led

01:16:39.060 --> 01:16:42.810 align:middle line:10%
by Defense Research Board
chief Vannevar Bush.

01:16:42.810 --> 01:16:44.500 align:middle line:10%
Sarbacher was still alive.

01:16:44.500 --> 01:16:49.260 align:middle line:10%
And when contacted, he confirmed
the contents of the Smith memo.

01:16:49.260 --> 01:16:53.220 align:middle line:10%
It seemed that a cover up was
finally beginning to unravel.

01:16:53.220 --> 01:16:54.510 align:middle line:90%
Then, in the mid-'80s--

01:16:54.510 --> 01:16:56.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Documents began to appear--

01:16:56.560 --> 01:17:00.570 align:middle line:84%
documents of unknown
provenance, for the most part.

01:17:00.570 --> 01:17:04.350 align:middle line:84%
>> The MJ-12 documents seem
to confirm the Roswell crash

01:17:04.350 --> 01:17:06.420 align:middle line:90%
in the New Mexico desert.

01:17:06.420 --> 01:17:08.910 align:middle line:84%
They purported to be an
eyes-only briefing given

01:17:08.910 --> 01:17:13.320 align:middle line:84%
in 1952 to Dwight Eisenhower
about Operation Majestic

01:17:13.320 --> 01:17:18.150 align:middle line:84%
12, an above top secret project
dealing with crashed saucers

01:17:18.150 --> 01:17:20.220 align:middle line:90%
and their occupants.

01:17:20.220 --> 01:17:23.310 align:middle line:84%
Prominently mentioned
was Dr. Vannevar Bush,

01:17:23.310 --> 01:17:26.790 align:middle line:84%
thus seeming to confirm
Wilbert Smith's memo.

01:17:26.790 --> 01:17:28.920 align:middle line:84%
Also present, others
who weighed heavily

01:17:28.920 --> 01:17:30.870 align:middle line:84%
in the history of
the phenomenon,

01:17:30.870 --> 01:17:34.080 align:middle line:84%
including the arch
debunker, Dr. Donald Menzel,

01:17:34.080 --> 01:17:36.240 align:middle line:84%
confirming many a
UFO researchers'

01:17:36.240 --> 01:17:41.460 align:middle line:84%
suspicion that debunkers are
really government agents.

01:17:41.460 --> 01:17:43.630 align:middle line:84%
For most researchers,
though, the documents

01:17:43.630 --> 01:17:45.370 align:middle line:90%
looked like a plant.

01:17:45.370 --> 01:17:49.000 align:middle line:84%
Suspicion fell on an agent named
Richard Doty in the Air Force

01:17:49.000 --> 01:17:52.060 align:middle line:84%
Office of Special Investigations
at Kirtland Air Force

01:17:52.060 --> 01:17:54.460 align:middle line:90%
Base near Albuquerque.

01:17:54.460 --> 01:17:56.440 align:middle line:84%
The Office of Special
Investigations

01:17:56.440 --> 01:17:59.750 align:middle line:84%
is the Air Force's
counterintelligence unit.

01:17:59.750 --> 01:18:02.920 align:middle line:84%
And a few years before,
at their Kirtland offices,

01:18:02.920 --> 01:18:05.680 align:middle line:84%
Doty had met with a
producer preparing a program

01:18:05.680 --> 01:18:08.940 align:middle line:90%
on UFOs for the HBO network.

01:18:08.940 --> 01:18:11.350 align:middle line:84%
And with cloak and
dagger theatrics,

01:18:11.350 --> 01:18:14.070 align:middle line:84%
he had shown her a
very similar document.

01:18:14.070 --> 01:18:17.590 align:middle line:10%
>> There it was,
written in dry English,

01:18:17.590 --> 01:18:20.950 align:middle line:10%
about the United States
government's efforts

01:18:20.950 --> 01:18:27.040 align:middle line:10%
to retrieve crashed disks
and non-human bodies,

01:18:27.040 --> 01:18:30.910 align:middle line:10%
both dead and alive, from
a variety of locations.

01:18:30.910 --> 01:18:34.120 align:middle line:84%
And I recall seven,
at least, were listed.

01:18:34.120 --> 01:18:37.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Linda Howe was also promised
long-rumored Air Force footage

01:18:37.780 --> 01:18:42.850 align:middle line:84%
of a UFO landing at White
Sands, New Mexico in 1964.

01:18:42.850 --> 01:18:46.360 align:middle line:84%
After a six-month runaround,
the footage never materialized,

01:18:46.360 --> 01:18:50.200 align:middle line:84%
and HBO canceled
her documentary.

01:18:50.200 --> 01:18:52.870 align:middle line:84%
With such a pedigree,
the MJ-12 documents

01:18:52.870 --> 01:18:56.440 align:middle line:84%
were suspected of being
disinformation, possibly

01:18:56.440 --> 01:18:59.140 align:middle line:84%
intended to keep the
increasing numbers of Roswell

01:18:59.140 --> 01:19:02.110 align:middle line:84%
researchers busy
chasing shadows,

01:19:02.110 --> 01:19:05.950 align:middle line:84%
and well away from whatever
real secrets the Air Force had,

01:19:05.950 --> 01:19:07.370 align:middle line:90%
UFOs or otherwise.

01:19:07.370 --> 01:19:08.170 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:19:08.170 --> 01:19:10.160 align:middle line:90%
>> "UFO Cover-Up, Live."

01:19:10.160 --> 01:19:13.360 align:middle line:84%
>> The following year, a Fox
television special claimed

01:19:13.360 --> 01:19:16.870 align:middle line:84%
to shed light on MJ-12
and the UFO cover-up.

01:19:16.870 --> 01:19:18.695 align:middle line:84%
>> How did you acquire
the MJ-12 documents?

01:19:18.695 --> 01:19:21.070 align:middle line:10%
>> They were mailed to me in
a plain brown envelope which

01:19:21.070 --> 01:19:21.640 align:middle line:10%
contained a--

01:19:21.640 --> 01:19:23.640 align:middle line:10%
>> The two researchers
who'd been the recipients

01:19:23.640 --> 01:19:27.160 align:middle line:10%
of the MJ-12 documents
introduced us to the Aviary.

01:19:27.160 --> 01:19:32.370 align:middle line:84%
>> MJ-12 was a group of
people within the government.

01:19:32.370 --> 01:19:34.930 align:middle line:84%
MJ-12 was created
by President Truman.

01:19:34.930 --> 01:19:37.350 align:middle line:10%
>> A silhouetted operative
codenamed Falcon,

01:19:37.350 --> 01:19:41.140 align:middle line:10%
claimed later by the producer
to be Richard Doty himself,

01:19:41.140 --> 01:19:44.920 align:middle line:10%
informed us of the structure
of MJ-12 and the startling news

01:19:44.920 --> 01:19:48.730 align:middle line:10%
that aliens had been held
since the Truman administration

01:19:48.730 --> 01:19:53.350 align:middle line:10%
in a top secret underground
installation called Area 51.

01:19:53.350 --> 01:19:57.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Their internal
organs are quite simple.

01:19:57.220 --> 01:20:00.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Among the details given about
their bodies, civilization,

01:20:00.490 --> 01:20:04.060 align:middle line:84%
and culture were their
partiality to Tibetan ritual

01:20:04.060 --> 01:20:07.010 align:middle line:90%
music and strawberry ice cream.

01:20:07.010 --> 01:20:10.120 align:middle line:84%
>> They have a religion, but
it's a universal religion.

01:20:10.120 --> 01:20:13.600 align:middle line:84%
>> It didn't really require an
alien crystal ball to perceive

01:20:13.600 --> 01:20:17.110 align:middle line:84%
that with this event, UFO
mythology was veering sharply

01:20:17.110 --> 01:20:20.080 align:middle line:84%
towards the
conspiratorial fringes.

01:20:20.080 --> 01:20:22.810 align:middle line:84%
Less evident was how much
this would be lapped up

01:20:22.810 --> 01:20:24.060 align:middle line:90%
by popular culture.

01:20:24.060 --> 01:20:27.294 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:20:27.294 --> 01:20:28.220 align:middle line:90%


01:20:28.220 --> 01:20:31.430 align:middle line:84%
Back in 1953, the
CIA Robertson Panel

01:20:31.430 --> 01:20:34.820 align:middle line:84%
had recommended debunking
the phenomenon's reality

01:20:34.820 --> 01:20:38.540 align:middle line:84%
and thereby its ability
to affect the population.

01:20:38.540 --> 01:20:41.780 align:middle line:10%
That had obviously failed.

01:20:41.780 --> 01:20:44.450 align:middle line:10%
Now, in the light of
the MJ-12 documents,

01:20:44.450 --> 01:20:46.730 align:middle line:10%
one had to wonder if
the phenomenon was being

01:20:46.730 --> 01:20:48.770 align:middle line:10%
deliberately manipulated--

01:20:48.770 --> 01:20:53.270 align:middle line:10%
possibly to hide any real UFO
secrets, but just as possibly

01:20:53.270 --> 01:20:57.140 align:middle line:10%
to provide a useful cover
for things more earthly,

01:20:57.140 --> 01:21:00.740 align:middle line:10%
like top secret black projects.

01:21:00.740 --> 01:21:03.770 align:middle line:84%
Whatever the reasons
behind the MJ-12 documents,

01:21:03.770 --> 01:21:06.500 align:middle line:84%
they did marginalize
UFO mythology

01:21:06.500 --> 01:21:10.190 align:middle line:84%
to the outer fringes of the
culture, which might have

01:21:10.190 --> 01:21:11.810 align:middle line:90%
been their intent all along.

01:21:11.810 --> 01:21:15.470 align:middle line:90%


01:21:15.470 --> 01:21:17.300 align:middle line:84%
But by happenstance,
the late '80s

01:21:17.300 --> 01:21:20.030 align:middle line:84%
saw a new wrinkle
in things that would

01:21:20.030 --> 01:21:22.400 align:middle line:90%
serve much the same purpose.

01:21:22.400 --> 01:21:26.030 align:middle line:10%
>> After 1987, the media
became much more interested

01:21:26.030 --> 01:21:28.760 align:middle line:10%
in the abduction phenomenon, and
there was sort of an avalanche

01:21:28.760 --> 01:21:30.920 align:middle line:10%
of shows that featured it.

01:21:30.920 --> 01:21:35.030 align:middle line:84%
It was a very good ratings
getter, and so forth.

01:21:35.030 --> 01:21:39.020 align:middle line:84%
>> UFO abductions seemed to
strike a deeply resonant chord

01:21:39.020 --> 01:21:43.070 align:middle line:84%
when they appeared in the mass
media in 1987 with the release

01:21:43.070 --> 01:21:44.630 align:middle line:90%
of two books.

01:21:44.630 --> 01:21:47.180 align:middle line:84%
Budd Hopkins's
"Intruders" expanded

01:21:47.180 --> 01:21:48.830 align:middle line:84%
on the similar
memories of people

01:21:48.830 --> 01:21:52.820 align:middle line:84%
who claim missing time
around a UFO encounter.

01:21:52.820 --> 01:21:56.000 align:middle line:84%
The aliens' interest in the
human reproductive system that

01:21:56.000 --> 01:21:58.550 align:middle line:84%
first appeared with the Betty
and Barney Hill incident

01:21:58.550 --> 01:22:01.850 align:middle line:84%
back in the '60s now
apparently included

01:22:01.850 --> 01:22:05.720 align:middle line:84%
a production line of hybrid
children, part human, part

01:22:05.720 --> 01:22:06.560 align:middle line:90%
alien.

01:22:06.560 --> 01:22:09.500 align:middle line:10%
>> I was, in a certain
sense, sticking my neck out,

01:22:09.500 --> 01:22:13.020 align:middle line:10%
because other researchers
are going to say, well,

01:22:13.020 --> 01:22:15.320 align:middle line:10%
I've never found anything
like this myself.

01:22:15.320 --> 01:22:17.660 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing to this.

01:22:17.660 --> 01:22:21.230 align:middle line:84%
Or counter-intuitive
evidence is going

01:22:21.230 --> 01:22:23.130 align:middle line:90%
to come forward, and so forth.

01:22:23.130 --> 01:22:27.920 align:middle line:84%
And yet in actual fact,
people began saying, my gosh.

01:22:27.920 --> 01:22:30.620 align:middle line:84%
When I explore
these other avenues,

01:22:30.620 --> 01:22:33.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm finding the
same thing he found.

01:22:33.470 --> 01:22:36.530 align:middle line:84%
>> At the same time,
almost in the same week,

01:22:36.530 --> 01:22:39.710 align:middle line:84%
the book "Communion" came
out, written by an abductee,

01:22:39.710 --> 01:22:42.620 align:middle line:84%
a person who claims to be an
abductee, Whitley Strieber.

01:22:42.620 --> 01:22:45.860 align:middle line:84%
And it hit the top of "The New
York Times" Best Seller list.

01:22:45.860 --> 01:22:49.490 align:middle line:84%
It was on "The New York Times"
Best Seller list for 32 weeks.

01:22:49.490 --> 01:22:53.270 align:middle line:84%
And it was number one in
the country for 19 weeks.

01:22:53.270 --> 01:22:58.250 align:middle line:84%
That book had a tremendous
impact societally.

01:22:58.250 --> 01:23:01.370 align:middle line:84%
And the impact was
not so much what

01:23:01.370 --> 01:23:04.610 align:middle line:84%
he had to say, which
was important enough,

01:23:04.610 --> 01:23:08.300 align:middle line:84%
but was the illustration
on the cover,

01:23:08.300 --> 01:23:14.360 align:middle line:84%
the sort of staring alien
that absolutely frightened

01:23:14.360 --> 01:23:16.220 align:middle line:84%
the devil out of
people who might

01:23:16.220 --> 01:23:17.960 align:middle line:90%
have had these experiences.

01:23:17.960 --> 01:23:19.790 align:middle line:90%
They became scared to death.

01:23:19.790 --> 01:23:21.880 align:middle line:84%
People told me they saw
the book in a bookstore,

01:23:21.880 --> 01:23:22.940 align:middle line:90%
and they just ran.

01:23:22.940 --> 01:23:25.640 align:middle line:84%
They ran out of the
mall and kept running.

01:23:25.640 --> 01:23:28.590 align:middle line:90%
They were so frightened.

01:23:28.590 --> 01:23:32.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Perhaps the "Communion" cover
art did somehow lift the veil

01:23:32.190 --> 01:23:34.380 align:middle line:90%
from repressed memories.

01:23:34.380 --> 01:23:36.720 align:middle line:84%
But the consistent
themes in the abduction

01:23:36.720 --> 01:23:38.850 align:middle line:84%
narrative also
appeared to express

01:23:38.850 --> 01:23:41.400 align:middle line:90%
the concerns of the times--

01:23:41.400 --> 01:23:43.830 align:middle line:84%
the individual's
loss of control,

01:23:43.830 --> 01:23:47.340 align:middle line:84%
genetic manipulation,
and the emerging worries

01:23:47.340 --> 01:23:49.500 align:middle line:90%
about the health of the earth.

01:23:49.500 --> 01:23:51.630 align:middle line:84%
Real or not, abductions
were touching

01:23:51.630 --> 01:23:53.160 align:middle line:90%
on something deeply mythic.

01:23:53.160 --> 01:23:56.630 align:middle line:90%


01:23:56.630 --> 01:23:58.790 align:middle line:84%
Up to this time,
crop circles had just

01:23:58.790 --> 01:24:04.120 align:middle line:84%
been indistinct ground markings,
apparently of landed saucers.

01:24:04.120 --> 01:24:07.090 align:middle line:84%
Now they began to appear
as elaborate mandalas,

01:24:07.090 --> 01:24:08.980 align:middle line:84%
mostly in England,
where it should

01:24:08.980 --> 01:24:13.320 align:middle line:84%
be noted that landscaping
is a form of religion.

01:24:13.320 --> 01:24:15.060 align:middle line:84%
Those who believe
some of the circles

01:24:15.060 --> 01:24:18.420 align:middle line:84%
were more than the work of
nocturnal serial artists

01:24:18.420 --> 01:24:22.347 align:middle line:84%
saw them as coded messages
from extraterrestrials.

01:24:22.347 --> 01:24:25.700 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:24:25.700 --> 01:24:29.540 align:middle line:90%


01:24:29.540 --> 01:24:32.720 align:middle line:10%
Also looking for coded messages
from the stars, the search

01:24:32.720 --> 01:24:36.560 align:middle line:10%
for extraterrestrial
intelligence, or SETI projects,

01:24:36.560 --> 01:24:39.000 align:middle line:10%
were getting underway.

01:24:39.000 --> 01:24:41.840 align:middle line:84%
One of the major objections
by the scientific community

01:24:41.840 --> 01:24:45.680 align:middle line:84%
to the idea of flying saucers
zipping around our planet

01:24:45.680 --> 01:24:47.600 align:middle line:84%
was the limiting
factor of the speed

01:24:47.600 --> 01:24:50.862 align:middle line:84%
of light, a consequence of
Einstein's special theory

01:24:50.862 --> 01:24:52.022 align:middle line:90%
of relativity.

01:24:52.022 --> 01:24:55.270 align:middle line:90%


01:24:55.270 --> 01:24:57.710 align:middle line:84%
If nothing could travel
faster than light,

01:24:57.710 --> 01:25:01.190 align:middle line:84%
a jaunt to just the nearest star
would take an absolute minimum

01:25:01.190 --> 01:25:02.420 align:middle line:90%
of 4 and 1/2 years.

01:25:02.420 --> 01:25:05.050 align:middle line:90%


01:25:05.050 --> 01:25:07.740 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, scientists reason,
that if anyone traveled

01:25:07.740 --> 01:25:10.980 align:middle line:84%
the vast distances, even
in our local neighborhood,

01:25:10.980 --> 01:25:14.130 align:middle line:90%
it would be very rarely.

01:25:14.130 --> 01:25:16.530 align:middle line:84%
And it wouldn't look
like the seeming traffic

01:25:16.530 --> 01:25:19.880 align:middle line:90%
jam being reported.

01:25:19.880 --> 01:25:22.360 align:middle line:84%
So SETI projects
started up with the idea

01:25:22.360 --> 01:25:26.050 align:middle line:84%
that smart aliens would
stay home and contact us

01:25:26.050 --> 01:25:32.530 align:middle line:84%
by an interstellar version of an
inexpensive long distance card.

01:25:32.530 --> 01:25:35.500 align:middle line:84%
Of course, all this assumes that
the speed of light cannot be

01:25:35.500 --> 01:25:40.600 align:middle line:84%
sidestepped in ways unknown
to our present physics.

01:25:40.600 --> 01:25:43.240 align:middle line:10%
Given the ever-changing
history of physical laws

01:25:43.240 --> 01:25:46.360 align:middle line:10%
over the last few hundred
years, that assumption

01:25:46.360 --> 01:25:50.080 align:middle line:10%
would appear to be more a
leap of faith than science.

01:25:50.080 --> 01:25:54.880 align:middle line:10%
>> It's also part of the
in-training of a scientist

01:25:54.880 --> 01:25:59.140 align:middle line:10%
to set borders on what
that scientist believes is

01:25:59.140 --> 01:26:01.750 align:middle line:10%
the nature of reality.

01:26:01.750 --> 01:26:05.140 align:middle line:84%
And it's a lot more comfortable,
if you have the arrogance

01:26:05.140 --> 01:26:07.690 align:middle line:84%
that you think you're
going to explain everything

01:26:07.690 --> 01:26:10.900 align:middle line:84%
sooner or later, to have a
rather narrow set of fences.

01:26:10.900 --> 01:26:13.920 align:middle line:90%


01:26:13.920 --> 01:26:16.830 align:middle line:84%
>> The early '90s saw growing
media fascination with

01:26:16.830 --> 01:26:18.840 align:middle line:90%
the Roswell incident.

01:26:18.840 --> 01:26:21.390 align:middle line:84%
New Mexico house
representative Steven Schiff

01:26:21.390 --> 01:26:26.190 align:middle line:84%
asked the Air Force about it and
hit a bureaucratic stonewall.

01:26:26.190 --> 01:26:28.020 align:middle line:10%
Annoyed by the lack
of response, he

01:26:28.020 --> 01:26:30.060 align:middle line:10%
requested the General
Accounting Office

01:26:30.060 --> 01:26:32.910 align:middle line:10%
to investigate Air Force
communications in and out

01:26:32.910 --> 01:26:36.420 align:middle line:10%
of Roswell in 1947.

01:26:36.420 --> 01:26:38.820 align:middle line:10%
The Air Force
subsequently decided

01:26:38.820 --> 01:26:42.310 align:middle line:10%
to conduct their own inquiry.

01:26:42.310 --> 01:26:44.520 align:middle line:84%
>> First of all, the
report was prepared

01:26:44.520 --> 01:26:48.240 align:middle line:84%
by counter-intelligence
people within the Air Force.

01:26:48.240 --> 01:26:54.080 align:middle line:10%
It's a case of the fox
guarding the henhouse, I think.

01:26:54.080 --> 01:26:57.100 align:middle line:10%
>> The Air Force report was
prepared by the same Pentagon

01:26:57.100 --> 01:27:00.820 align:middle line:10%
personnel that many researchers
believe had authored the MJ-12

01:27:00.820 --> 01:27:02.530 align:middle line:10%
documents.

01:27:02.530 --> 01:27:07.090 align:middle line:84%
Its 998 pages concluded that
there was indeed a cover up.

01:27:07.090 --> 01:27:10.720 align:middle line:84%
But it was only of debris from
a secret Project Mogul balloon

01:27:10.720 --> 01:27:13.430 align:middle line:90%
launch that had gone missing.

01:27:13.430 --> 01:27:15.580 align:middle line:10%
Moguls were huge
balloon assemblies

01:27:15.580 --> 01:27:18.430 align:middle line:10%
intended to explore the
possibility of remotely

01:27:18.430 --> 01:27:22.690 align:middle line:10%
monitoring Soviet A-bomb tests.

01:27:22.690 --> 01:27:26.230 align:middle line:84%
But there were multiple
problems with the explanation.

01:27:26.230 --> 01:27:29.110 align:middle line:84%
First of all, there was no
definitive evidence outside

01:27:29.110 --> 01:27:31.960 align:middle line:84%
of one scientist's
50-year-old memory

01:27:31.960 --> 01:27:36.160 align:middle line:84%
that the particular Mogul
launch had ever taken place.

01:27:36.160 --> 01:27:39.460 align:middle line:10%
And then, even leaving aside
the multiple witness testimony

01:27:39.460 --> 01:27:41.830 align:middle line:10%
about the unearthly
nature of the material

01:27:41.830 --> 01:27:45.850 align:middle line:10%
recovered, the apparent size
and secrecy of the recovery

01:27:45.850 --> 01:27:49.030 align:middle line:10%
operation itself, and
the reported threats

01:27:49.030 --> 01:27:51.880 align:middle line:10%
made to witnesses
about keeping silent,

01:27:51.880 --> 01:27:54.910 align:middle line:10%
there remain the simple
fact that Mogul assemblies

01:27:54.910 --> 01:27:58.870 align:middle line:10%
were mostly weather balloons,
tin foil and balsa wood.

01:27:58.870 --> 01:28:01.780 align:middle line:84%
So how would the chief
intelligence officer as well as

01:28:01.780 --> 01:28:05.320 align:middle line:84%
the base commander mistake
such mundane material

01:28:05.320 --> 01:28:09.160 align:middle line:84%
and announce it to the
world as a flying saucer?

01:28:09.160 --> 01:28:12.190 align:middle line:84%
Also somewhat damning was that
the General Accounting Office

01:28:12.190 --> 01:28:15.070 align:middle line:84%
found that all communications
in and out of the Roswell

01:28:15.070 --> 01:28:17.680 align:middle line:84%
base for the period
had been destroyed

01:28:17.680 --> 01:28:20.740 align:middle line:90%
without authorization.

01:28:20.740 --> 01:28:25.930 align:middle line:84%
But as there was no smoking, gun
Roswell would remain a mystery.

01:28:25.930 --> 01:28:29.110 align:middle line:84%
Whatever came down in
the desert back in 1947

01:28:29.110 --> 01:28:32.470 align:middle line:84%
would continue to be
obscured by an expanding

01:28:32.470 --> 01:28:36.730 align:middle line:84%
tangle of testimony,
by suspect documents,

01:28:36.730 --> 01:28:40.441 align:middle line:84%
and by what would become
the UFO hoax of all time.

01:28:40.441 --> 01:28:43.740 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:28:43.740 --> 01:28:46.770 align:middle line:84%
In 1995, Fox broadcast
what purported

01:28:46.770 --> 01:28:50.910 align:middle line:84%
to be film of a
Roswell alien autopsy.

01:28:50.910 --> 01:28:51.930 align:middle line:90%
Is it faked?

01:28:51.930 --> 01:28:53.780 align:middle line:90%
the program asked.

01:28:53.780 --> 01:28:56.280 align:middle line:84%
But the question was
really rhetorical,

01:28:56.280 --> 01:29:01.070 align:middle line:84%
as the only required answer
was enormous ratings.

01:29:01.070 --> 01:29:05.330 align:middle line:84%
As tabloid TV was feasting
like zombies on UFOs,

01:29:05.330 --> 01:29:07.520 align:middle line:84%
the mainstream media
apparently decided

01:29:07.520 --> 01:29:09.800 align:middle line:84%
to rise above the
silliness, and they

01:29:09.800 --> 01:29:13.380 align:middle line:84%
stopped reporting UFO
sightings altogether,

01:29:13.380 --> 01:29:18.000 align:middle line:84%
even ones that were
quite spectacular.

01:29:18.000 --> 01:29:21.870 align:middle line:10%
In a 1996 incident in
the Yukon, 31 people

01:29:21.870 --> 01:29:26.130 align:middle line:10%
in four different groups
along a 340-kilometer stretch

01:29:26.130 --> 01:29:30.120 align:middle line:10%
of the Klondike highway
described an enormous object,

01:29:30.120 --> 01:29:34.840 align:middle line:10%
triangulated later at up to
two kilometers in diameter.

01:29:34.840 --> 01:29:38.730 align:middle line:10%
It went virtually unreported
in the national media.

01:29:38.730 --> 01:29:40.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh my God.

01:29:40.170 --> 01:29:41.610 align:middle line:90%
>> What the hell are you doing?

01:29:41.610 --> 01:29:42.818 align:middle line:90%
Get back in the car, asshole!

01:29:42.818 --> 01:29:45.510 align:middle line:84%
>> But if the major news outlets
now ignored UFO accounts,

01:29:45.510 --> 01:29:49.140 align:middle line:84%
Hollywood executives had no
problems distorting them.

01:29:49.140 --> 01:29:54.320 align:middle line:84%
"Fire in the Sky" portrayed
the Travis Walton incident.

01:29:54.320 --> 01:29:56.270 align:middle line:10%
>> While we were preparing
"Fire in the Sky"

01:29:56.270 --> 01:29:59.510 align:middle line:10%
to go before the cameras, some
of the executives at Paramount

01:29:59.510 --> 01:30:02.480 align:middle line:10%
suddenly came in the next day
with this great revelation.

01:30:02.480 --> 01:30:04.190 align:middle line:10%
